title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meats thoroughly with bread which has been soaked in water or milk.
Add seasonings and beaten eggs.
Pack into a well-greased loaf pan.
Spread with the catsup or chili sauce and bake in a moderate oven, 375°, for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In a large pan, boil water, celery, onion and bouillon cube for 20 minutes. Add vegetables and potatoes. Cook 30 minutes. Place in crock-pot. Add cream of chicken soup and cheese. Cook on low until vegetables are tender. Stir periodically.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: On waxed paper combine flour, sage and thyme.
Coat chicken lightly with flour mixture.
In skillet over medium-high heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken until browned bits.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve hot over cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible ham and swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms(low-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems and chop finely.
Heat oil in a skillet.
Add onion and saute about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add chopped mushroom stems and zucchini and saute 5 minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients and remove from heat. Stuff mushroom caps with mixture and place on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk and butter in saucepan over a low heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter over filling.
Sprinkle with remaining cup of nuts.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Cool thoroughly, preferably overnight, before slicing.

title: chili mexican dip
directions: In 8 x 8-inch pan, spread cream cheese in bottom of pan. Spread chili on top of cream cheese evenly.
Spread salsa on top of chili.
Grate cheese and spread on top.
Place in oven at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cheese must be melted.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Bake chocolate chip cake according to box directions.
Cool. Cut into cubes.
Pour 1 1/2 c. milk into medium bowl.
Add chocolate pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.	Gently stir in 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Do the same with vanilla pudding mix.
Arrange 1/2 of cake cubes in a 3 1/2 quart serving bowl.
Drizzle with 1/2 of chocolate syrup.
Layer with 1/2 of chopped candy bars and chocolate pudding.
Repeat layers, ending with vanilla pudding.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Sprinkle with additional chopped candy bars.

title: chicken gizzards and hominy
directions: Season gizzards with seasoned salt (or salt and pepper if preferred) and dredge in sufficient flour to cover gizzards. Brown in pan with oil until almost tender.
Add can mushrooms, including liquid, and cook with lid on until tender.
Add hominy and stir until heated and mixture becomes thickened.
Will serve 2 or 3.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt; stir in softened butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in 1 cup warm water.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add mashed potatoes.
This batter should be thicker than cake batter but pourable.
Add a little water if necessary.
Allow to rise in mixing bowl until double, 1 to 2 hours.
Stir down gently.
Pour into a 17 x 11-inch greased pan.
Let rise again.
Top with brown sugar and cinnamon; dot with butter.
Pinch gently with fingers.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
While cooling, pour mix of 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup milk or cream over cake.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°, or until done. Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: chicken licking good pork chops
directions: Dredge pork chops in mixture of ingredients, then brown in 2 tablespoons oil.
Put in crock-pot with 1 can chicken with rice soup.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or 3 1/2 hours on high.

title: butter mints
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until blended.
Add a small amount of food coloring and mix until blended.
Press mixture into mint molds or roll into small balls and flatten slightly.

title: chocolate chip pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and egg.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with pumpkin, vanilla, chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: If using fresh carrots, cook until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator at least 12 hours.
You can drain carrots and use the liquid for salad dressing.

title: strata
directions: In medium frypan, cook mushrooms, onion and marjoram with 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Spread remaining butter over one side of each bread slice.
Cut bread in 1/2-inch cubes.
Arrange 1/2 of the cubes over bottom of casserole.
Pour mushroom mixture over bread cubes.
Thoroughly combine cheeses and dry mustard and sprinkle over mushroom mixture in dish.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Blend together remaining ingredients and pour over bread mixture in dish.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Uncover dish and bake in preheated oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: frosting for chocolate cake
directions: Cook milk and flour in a small saucepan until begins
to boil and forms a thick sauce.
Allow to cool.
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until smooth.
Add cooled sauce and vanilla and continue to beat until frosting is creamy.
Frost cake. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Punch holes in top of cake.
Spread crushed pineapple on top.
Spread crushed softened cream cheese over pineapple.
Spread instant pudding over cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and top with coconut.

title: small pecan pies
directions: Place tart shells
on
cookie
sheet.
Mix all ingredients, pour into shells, adding pecans on top if desired.
Bake at 425° for 10
minutes;
reduce heat to 325°, bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs until light and foamy, then add oil, sugar, zucchini, and vanilla mixing lightly.
Add dry ingredients mixing well, then stir in nuts.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: rice pilaf(great vegetarian dish!)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine boiling water and butter; stir until butter is melted.
Stir in brown rice, wild rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover; bake at 375° for 70 minutes.
Stir in carrot and frozen peas.
Cover and bake about 10 minutes or until rice is tender.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: rehruecken mit aepfeln und preiselbeeren(saddle of venison with apples and lingonberries)
directions: To serve 6 to 8, use a well-aged 5-pound saddle of venison.
If saddle of venison is not available, a 4 to 5 pound boned and rolled venison leg or shoulder roast may be substituted.
Saddle of venison should be marinated either in sour milk or in juice of 1 lemon and 1/2 cup olive oil for at least 3 hours.
Lard the venison in even rows with strips of larding pork 2-inches long.

Crush 1 teaspoon juniper berries with 1 teaspoon salt and rub into meat. Lay venison, larded side down, in a roasting pan, add 1 onion, separated in rings, a 3-inch curl of lemon peel and 1/2 cup vinegar.
Pour 1/2 cup simmering melted butter over the meat. Roast for 15 minutes in a moderate oven (350°).
Pour over it 1 cup sour cream, roast for 45 minutes more, basting frequently.
Add 1 more cup hot sour cream during roasting.
Turn venison, continue to roast.
Allow 20 minutes per pound for medium rare.
A pinch of curry powder can be added towards the end; garnish with boiled apples and lingonberries.
Peel 4 medium-sized apples, cut in half and core.
Boil in water with vinegar, until tender, but so that they do not lose shape after removing.
Let cool.
Fill with lingonberries.

title: tea cakes(100 year old recipe)
directions: This is how tea cakes were made over 100 years ago by using a wooden bread tray (I still have mine).
Don't use a spoon; mix with your hand.
You sift flour in bread tray and make a hole in middle of flour.
Break eggs and put in hole, then add sugar and flavoring in hole.
Put a big handful of Crisco on top.
Add a little milk if needed.
Mix it real well with hand, taking up as much flour as you needed or until you can feel the grains of sugar, then knead until you can make biscuits.
Pinch off little pieces big enough to make a biscuit.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Mix remaining ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls on top of cake mix.
Swirl with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: natillas(soft custard)
directions: Place egg yolks, flour and 1 cup of milk in a small mixing bowl.
Stir to make a smooth paste.
Set aside.
Place the remaining milk, sugar and salt in a medium sized saucepan and scald at medium heat.
Add the egg mixture to the scalded milk and continue to cook at medium heat until a soft custard consistency is reached.
Remove custard from heat and allow to cool to room temperature.
Beat the egg whites in a medium sized mixing bowl until they are stiff, but not dry.
Fold the egg whites into the custard.
Chill and garnish with nutmeg and cinnamon before serving.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in baking dish at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In each of 12 medium muffin cups, place 2 teaspoons butter and brown sugar.
Place in oven to melt.
Mix remaining ingredients, except pecan halves; beat vigorously 1/2 minute.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips; turn into buttered shallow 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine cheese and potato chips and spread over top.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry mold
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Save a few strawberries to garnish the mold.
Place in refrigerator until it's the consistency of jelly.
Remove; add 1/2 pint of sour cream which has been beaten for 4 to 5 minutes.
Blend and serve with fresh strawberries.
Beautiful!

title: pumpkin dip (spread)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with graham crackers or gingersnap cookies.

title: ham and lima bean salad
directions: Cook lima beans according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
In a mixing bowl, combine mushrooms, onion, ham, olives, parsley and pimiento.

title: heavenly chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground chuck with soup mix (or Mrs. Grass onion mix). Add tomato sauce, and if need more liquid add catsup, and brown sugar (more or less how sweet you like).
Simmer.
Good next day or freeze.

title: chocolate peanut butter rice krispies treats
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often.
Continue until it boils.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add Rice Krispies, coating well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chips together in microwave until smooth.
Pour over Rice Krispies.

title: gazpacho
directions: In small saucepan, cook garlic in olive oil.
Combine in a large bowl with soup, water and vinegar.
Chill for 4 hours. Serve in chilled bowls.
Pass chilled vegetables and croutons for garnish.
Makes about 6 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate oats candy
directions: Bring sugar, milk, cocoa and butter to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Keep stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oats. Mix well.
Then drop by tablespoonful on wax paper and cool.

title: sweet and spicy hot dogs
directions: Heat jelly and cocktail sauce on stove top.
Slice hot dogs into 1-inch links; mix with sauce.
Cook on medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in large bowl.
Cover with a mixture of 9 ingredients.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for 36 to 48 hours, turning meat 1 or 2 times a day.
Remove meat.
Pat dry, rub lightly with flour and brown well in hot fat.
Strain vinegar mixture and add to meat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender (about 3 or 4 hours).
Remove meat; keep warm.
For gravy, skim excess liquid from pan.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs; mix lightly.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour.
Set aside.
Mix 3 cubes chicken bouillon into 2 cups of hot water.
Pour into the flour and margarine for sauce.
Cook until it thickens.
Stir in the can of green chiles and sour cream.
Pour over top of the tortillas. Sprinkle lightly with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix margarine, cheese, onion, eggs and thawed broccoli.
Then add muffin mix last.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Wash potatoes and scrub skins clean.
Peel and quarter and wash again.
Put potatoes in pot.
Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste, 1 can of beef (diced up) and 1 onion.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Serve hot.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease muffin cups with butter.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place the pieces into pan.
Sprinkle sugar onto biscuit pieces.
Sprinkle cinnamon onto biscuit pieces. Put into oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: creole crappie
directions: In a pot over medium heat, place oil and add flour, stirring until it makes a dark brown roux.
Add chopped onion, pepper and celery.
Gradually add chicken stock and white wine while stirring gently.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Cut fillets into chunks and place them in an oiled casserole dish.
Sprinkle fish with last 5 ingredients; then pour contents of pot into casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Mix and add to jello.
Gel completely.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Spray inside of brown grocery bag with vegetable spray.
Put popcorn in bag.
In large bowl, microwave brown sugar, syrup and margarine for 2 to 4 minutes until rapid boil.
Stir once.
Add baking soda.
Stir for 1 minute.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Roll up bag and shake.
Prick bag 3 or 4 times.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain. Saute mushrooms and onion in skillet until tender.
Add Italian seasoning; mix well.
Melt margarine over low heat in large saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper gradually until smooth; stir in milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese. Squeeze spinach dry.
Chop spinach and broccoli.
Combine with carrots in bowl; mix well.
Combine Ricotta cheese and egg in bowl; mix well.
Layer 1 cup white sauce, vegetables, noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture, mushroom mixture and remaining white sauce in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Loosen sides of loaf pan.
Remove to cooling rack.
Cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate no longer than 1 week.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Combine.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° in an iron skillet.

title: tuna pie
directions: Prepare pie crust as directed.
Cover dough and set aside. In a large skillet, cook onion and margarine until tender; add potato and water.
Cover and simmer until potato is tender.
Stir in soup, milk, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, dill and pepper.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in frozen veggies and tuna.
Spoon into ungreased casserole dish.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Heat milk and spices in a saucepan over medium heat to just below boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer.
Finely chop onion and saute in 1/2 tablespoon butter on medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add to saucepan.
Combine the remaining 1 tablespoon melted butter with the flour in a small saute pan. (This is the first step of making a roux, which will thicken the sauce.)
Mix until completely blended; cook on low heat 3 to 4 minutes to make roux.
Add roux to saucepan and mix well. Continue to cook until sauce thickens.
Cut the Cheddar, Jack and Velveeta cheeses into small cubes and add to saucepan.
Heat over low heat and slowly stir until cheese is melted.
Be careful not to burn the sauce.
Remove from heat and cool 15 minutes.
Drain artichokes and gently squeeze the water out of them.
Cut the artichokes into 1/4-inch strips.
Set aside.
Squeeze as much water as possible out of the spinach.
Add spinach and artichokes to sauce mix.
Mix until completely blended.
Transfer to a 8 x 8 x 2 casserole dish and top with grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips, sour cream and salsa.

title: red bean shortbread delight
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla and stir.
Add flour and mix well.
Place half of dough in a greased 9 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan.
Spread dough to cover bottom of the pan. Then spread red bean mixture over dough.
Top with remaining dough.
Beat 1 egg and brush the top of dough.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter and stir in sugar. Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together and add to butter mixture. Add chocolate chips and nuts. Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: busy day burgers
directions: Brown and crumble in skillet the ground beef.
Stir in flour. When flour has been completely dissolved, stir in onion soup. Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve on buns or over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together with just enough buttermilk to hold it together.
For best results, chill for 1 or 2 hours before cooking.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Into large bowl measure all ingredients.
With mixer at medium speed, beat ingredients until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
With hands shape dough into ball. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours, until easy to handle.
Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Roll half or 1/3 dough at a time, keeping remainder refrigerated.
For crisp cookies, roll dough paper thin.
For softer cookies, roll 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick. With floured cookie cutter, cut into various shapes.
Re-roll trimmings and cut. Place cookies 1/2 inch apart on cookie sheets. Sprinkle with decorative toppings.
Bake 8 minutes or until very light brown.
With spatula remove cookies to racks and cool. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: greyfield inn chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Butter sides of 10-inch spring-form pan. Shake some crumbs around the pan to coat the sides.
Add melted butter to rest of crumbs.
Blend well. Press over bottom of pan.

title: cream-style corn(frozen and cook)
directions: Cut and scrape corn from cob.
Add water if too thick. Microwave on High 5 minutes at a time, stirring after 5 minutes, until corn is hot and changed colors.
If you want to freeze, stop here, cool and bag when cool.
To cook, cook until corn is tender. Add salt, pepper and butter.
If not real sweet corn, add sugar. If too thin, dissolve the cornstarch in a little hot water and stir into corn to thicken.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour one stick melted butter over the crackers.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: french vanilla torte
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Make pudding as on box.
Melt chocolate in double boiler with margarine, milk and xxx sugar.
Watch that chocolate doesn't burn.
Layer as follows: graham crackers, 1/2 pudding, graham crackers and rest of pudding. Drizzle chocolate over all.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.
Place a dollop of Cool Whip on top before serving.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Blend melted butter with all-purpose flour.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until sauce is thick.
Add salt, diced and cooked chicken, broiled and sliced mushrooms (drained) and chopped pimiento.
Heat through.
Serve over hot toast points.
Makes 5 servings.

title: railroad slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage with onion and sugar.
Pan mix together rest of ingredients.
Stir often.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cabbage. Mix well.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Add carrots, if desired.

title: near east shrimp(low-fat)
directions: Coat a wok with cooking spray.
Add a teaspoon of oil.
Allow to heat for 2 minutes.
Add vegetables and stir-fry for 3 minutes. Remove vegetables.
Add 2 teaspoons of oil to wok and stir-fry shrimp for 3 minutes.
Reduce heat, add vegetables and sauce to taste; cook an additional 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with nuts and ginger and serve immediately.
Can be served over rice.
Yield: 6 servings (218 calories, without rice).

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and butter or margarine. Add Cool Whip.
Mix vanilla pudding, cold milk and vanilla. Combine with cream cheese mixture and divide into 1/2.
Layer cake, beginning with cookies, followed by 1/2 of the mixture.
Repeat.

title: granola cereal
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
(Baking time:
20 minutes.)
Mix all dry ingredients together in largest cake pan you have.
In a 2-cup measuring cup, first add oil, then honey, then vanilla (mixing in this order keeps honey from sticking to cup).
Gradually pour liquid into dry ingredients, mixing with hands or stirring thoroughly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix broth from chicken with chicken soup.
Layer half of chicken, 1/3 stuffing, half of chicken and soup in a large casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Spread mushroom soup on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef until done.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, basil and oregano.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° or 325° if glass dish.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large bowl on High for 2 minutes or until melted. Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.

title: piccadilly shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Combine paprika, Ro-Tel tomatoes and soup.
Add to vegetables and cook 20 minutes. Add parsley and continue to cook 10 more minutes.
Add shrimp to sauce and allow to blend about 15 more minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: jambalaya
directions: Boil chicken in 3 to 4 cups water with some chopped onion and celery added.
Save broth.
Debone chicken.
In large skillet, brown sausage.
Add chopped vegetables and rice in sausage and drippings.
Add 3 cups chicken broth.
Add spices.
Cover and simmer until rice is done (about 40 minutes).
Add chicken midway. Serves 6.

title: coquille st. jacques
directions: If large scallops are used, cut into 3 or 4 pieces.
In a medium saucepan, cook and stir minced onions in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Add scallops, lemon juice, salt, paprika and wine. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms; simmer 2 minutes. Drain liquid and set aside.
Melt 1/3 cup butter in medium pan over low heat.
Blend in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in reserved liquid and heavy cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add parsley.
Reserving 1/2 cup of sauce in saucepan, pour remainder over scallops, mushrooms mixture.
Heat through, stirring frequently.
Spoon mixture into 6 individual baking shells.
Spread each with 1 tablespoon reserve sauce.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in small skillet and add crumbs, stirring until brown.
Place shells on baking sheet and oven broil 5-inches from heat, 5 to 8 minutes until brown.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread layer of cream cheese in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Next, spread layer of chili, then add layer of picante sauce (use as much or as little as you would like).
Add a few chopped chili peppers on top of sauce layer.
Top with shredded Chi Chi Mexican cheese.

title: super easy pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix vegetables and soup in 9-inch pie plate or casserole dish.
Stir remaining ingredients in separate bowl until well blended.
Pour over top of vegetable/soup mix. Bake about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: diabetic chocolate pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, honey and Rice Krispies well and press into pie pan. Slice the bananas over the crust.
Mix the pudding and milk and pour over the bananas. Refrigerate 30 minutes until pudding gets firm.
Spread with the Cool Whip.

title: onion-vegetable soup
directions: Grate all of the vegetables coarsely, but not too coarse. Place all of the ingredients with 1 quart of water in a pan; boil lightly for 1/2 hour.
The Tabasco and Worcestershire can be added later in the process so the taste will not be overpowering.
Taste it during the 1/2-hour period and add whatever makes it taste good.
This includes more water to make it as loose as you like it.

title: molasses cookies(roll out)
directions: Melt and cool shortening.
Mix together ingredients.
Add 5 cups of flour.
Blend together.
Roll out and sprinkle with sugar. Cut out and bake for 8 to 10 minutes in oven at 425°.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Put one container of sherbet into punch bowl. Add 1 can juice and 1 bottle ginger ale. Stir to mix to slushy consistency. Add more juice, drink and sherbet as necessary. Makes 50 servings. Preparation time: 0:30.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients except crab and 1/4 cup cheese, until well blended.
Add crab and top with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Do not cover.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Wash
and
remove seed from peppers.
Grind peppers and combine
with
sugar and vinegar in a large saucepan.
Heat to boiling and let boil for 1 minute, stirring to prevent boiling over.
Remove
from
heat.	Stir
in pectin, mixing well.
Let stand
minutes.	Skim film from top.
Mix in food coloring. Strain
to	remove pieces of pepper.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Top with sterilized two part lids and tighten.
Cool on racks.
This
makes six 8 ounce jars and is good with crackers or scrambled eggs.

title: cherry delights
directions: Mix Mazola margarine and sugar.
Stir in Karo light syrup, egg yolks and flour.
Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg whites, then nuts.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Press candied cherry halves into centers.
Bake in 325° oven 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the egg yolks, cornstarch and 1 cup of the heavy cream. Whisk to blend well. Set aside. Combine 2 cups cream, 1 1/2 cups sugar and the vanilla bean in a large heavy-bottom saucepan over medium heat. Whisk to dissolve the sugar and bring to a gentle boil, about 10 minutes. Slowly add the egg yolk mixture, whisking constantly, until it thickens, about 5 minutes. Be forewarned:

The mixture will break; don't be alarmed. Pour it into a glass bowl. Press a piece of plastic wrap down over the surface of the mixture to prevent a skin from forming. Let cool completely at room temperature.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spread evenly over potatoes and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: boiled ham dinner
directions: Simmer a picnic or ham hock with a lot of ham left on it; add no salt.
Add the carrots, turnips, onions and potatoes.
Cook until vegetables are done.

title: sticky buns
directions: Butter pan.
Sprinkle raisins and walnuts on bottom of pan. Pour a little pancake syrup on top.
Lay in rolls.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese. Add biscuit mix and blend thoroughly. Shape into 1-inch balls on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 minutes or until brown. Serve warm or cold.
Yields 100.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift cocoa with 1/3 cup sugar.
Add scalded milk gradually and stir until smooth.
Cool.
Combine shortening, salt and vanilla. Add 1 cup sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add soda to flour and sift three times.
Add flour to creamed mixture, mixing after each addition until smooth.
Pour into two 9-inch layer pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into mold. Refrigerate until set. Serves 8.

title: ohio valley pioneers hot party canapes
directions: Combine Swiss cheese, mayonnaise, cream cheese, mustard, salad dressing and lemon juice in a bowl; mix well.
Fold in bacon. Spread generously on a choice of party bread slices.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Broil until light brown.
Serve immediately.

title: bear in a pit(traditional)
directions: Dig a pit 2 1/2 feet wide by 2 feet deep.
Line the pit with 8 to 10 layers of green maple leaves.
Place bear meat chunks on leaves; add cut up pumpkin.
Cover with several layers of leaves. Cover with stones. Build a fire and burn until coals are covered with embers.
Cover with dirt and cook for 4 to 5 hours.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine sugar, molasses and water in a saucepan and bring to soft ball stage (235°).
Remove from heat and add soda.
Mix popped corn with peanuts and pour sugar mixture over all.
Stir to coat evenly.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: easy lemon cookies
directions: Form the mixture into one-inch balls, pressing firmly.
Place the balls two inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes until golden brown around the edges. Cool for one minute and remove from the cookie sheet.
Makes three to four dozen cookies.

title: mama's sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mash the potatoes.
Add sugar, flour, butter, vanilla and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in milk. Spread mixture into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until set.

title: brownies
directions: Sift sugar and flour together in a bowl and set aside.
In a saucepan, mix margarine, shortening, cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Add milk, eggs, baking soda and salt.
Pour into a well-greased brownie pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: meaty cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in a large skillet, stirring until it is crumbled.
Drain and return to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Cream the softened butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add gradually. Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Delicious plain or served with fruit or sauce.

title: mom's waffles
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Beat only until mixed barely.
(Don't overbeat!)
Place on hot waffle iron.
Makes 8 to 10 waffles.
Cut in half for small family.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger, baking powder and cloves into bowl and mix well.
Combine sugar, oil, pumpkin, eggs and nuts in a bowl and mix well.
Add the flour mixture, stirring until blended.
Stir in water.
Spoon into two 1-1/2 pound loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand in pan until cool. Good with flavored cream cheese.

title: creamy shrimp fettuccine(low-fat recipe)
directions: Saute shrimp and garlic in liquid Butter Buds or fat-free chicken broth until shrimp are pink.
Stir in tomatoes; simmer 5 minutes.
Blend in skim milk, flour and green onions.
Add red pepper now if you are using it.
Sprinkle in Parmesan cheese. Heat until smooth and blended.
Do not boil.
Serve over cooked fettuccine.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and slice pickles and onions.
Soak in salt water about 4 hours.
While pickles are soaking, bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil, then set aside to cool.
Drain pickles well (squeeze juice out).
Place pickles in jars.
Pour brine over pickles.
Put caps on, but do not worry about sealing.
Place in refrigerator. Let stand a couple of weeks before using.

title: lela's chocolate or coconut pie
directions: Cook filling of choice in an IRON SKILLET! Combine dry ingredients in the skillet. Add milk and margarine, cook low to med. heat. Gradually add beaten egg yolks and vanilla. Stir throughout the cooking time. Cook until thick. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
(For coconut pie, put all the coconut you want in the filling, and sprinkle coconut on top of meringue.)

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine rice and pimentos; place 1/3 of rice mixture in greased casserole.
Alternate layers of remaining rice, chicken, mushrooms and almonds.
Pour over chicken broth, seasoned with salt and pepper; blend with flour.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffing spinach balls
directions: Cook onion with spinach.
Drain well.
Chop spinach.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 -15 minutes at 350° or until golden brown. Or roll into ball and freeze, or bake balls and freeze.
Makes 50 balls.
Do not thaw to bake or heat.

title: easy coconut macaroons
directions: Combine condensed milk, coconut and vanilla in bowl; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Remove macaroons from cookie sheet immediately.
Yield: 8 dozen.

title: braised venison chops
directions: Roll chops in flour well seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown well in shortening.
Add 1/2 cup water and simmer until tender. Pour 1 cup Burgundy or Claret wine over chops and cook down until almost dry.
Remove chops and make gravy, adding 1 small can of mushrooms.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Pour gravy over chops before serving.

title: ron's taco lasagna
directions: Brown meat with taco seasoning and drain.
Place 1 tortilla on pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Spread refried beans 1/4 -inch thick over tortilla.
Cover with another shell.
Spread taco meat over shell. Add another shell.
Cover with layer of sour cream, lettuce, tomato and olives.
Add shell.
Pour on salsa and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool for 3 to 5 minutes.
Cut like pie and serve.
Serves 6.

title: peach pie
directions: Pour peaches into a casserole dish.
Spread yellow cake mix over peaches. Slice butter into cubes and arrange over the top of yellow cake mix.
Put into preheated oven at 350° and cook until light golden brown on top or usually until bubbling.

title: fresh blueberry jam
directions: Place berries and syrup in saucepan.
Add gelatin dissolved in water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 6 to 8 minutes. Pour into jar.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: elk green chili casserole
directions: Fry meat (elk) in oil.
Chop onion and garlic.
Add to cooked meat.
Add chili and mix well.
You can use frozen or roasted fresh green chilies, whichever you desire.

title: never fail squash casserole
directions: Wash and cut off ends of squash.
Slice and boil along with chopped onion for about 30 to 45 minutes or until done; strain. Put cooked squash and onions in mixing bowl.
Add butter, salt and pepper, beaten eggs, bread crumbs and dash of Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Put pineapple and juice in saucepan and heat.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Add buttermilk and cool.
When cool, stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Skin, cool and cut up into bite size pieces.
Place in 3-quart baking dish.
Pour 1 cup broth and soups over chicken.
Melt margarine; mix with 1 cup broth and stir in stuffing.
Mix well and pour over top. Do not stir.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix sauce ingredients well.
Pour over ham ball to cover.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: To these ingredients, add enough milk to make a batter; beat. Place in a baking dish and bake to consistency of a custard.
Put marshmallows on top and brown the last few minutes of baking. Bake at 325°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion
is tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 10 minutes or until thick.
Add to 5 pounds cooked cold ribs and heat.

title: gorp(trail mix)
directions: Mix all together and place in plastic Ziploc bag. Can be divided and put into smaller Ziploc bags.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Combine onions and spread in bottom of pan.
Drain Veg-All and mix with soup.
Pour over mixture.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in baking pan in order given.
Place in oven until the cheese on top is melted (or microwave).
Top with hot red pepper. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oatmeal chocolate chippers
directions: Thoroughly cream together the shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats, nuts and chocolate.
If desired, chill dough for easy handling. Shape dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten balls with bottom of a sugar coated glass. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend together in blender on high for 30 seconds.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 9 cups of boiling water.
Set aside and let cool.
Dissolve sugar in 4 cups of warm water and add Jell-O. Cool.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix well.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put together butter in baking dish; let melt in oven.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, 3/4 cup sugar and milk together; beat well.
Pour batter over butter and add fruit.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit drop cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well and add nuts, dates, mixed fruit and raisins.
Combine with dry ingredients and mix all very well.
Grease cookie sheets.
Drop by spoonful.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Yields 16 - 18 dozen depending on size.
Delicious and stores well in a tupperware container.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook together for 15 minutes. Add cream and cook until potatoes are tender.
Serve hot.
Garnish with parsley.

title: mexican bahita's
directions: Slice meat across grain 1/8 inch thick.
Marinate in mixture of garlic, oregano, cumin, salt, orange juice, vinegar and hot pepper sauce for 10 minutes.
Stir-fry meat in oil in hot skillet until done.
The last couple of minutes add the onion and pepper. When meat is done and onion and pepper are of desired tenderness, wrap in tortillas.
Place cheese over the top and bake in 400° oven until melted.
Garnish with lettuce, green onion tops, tomatoes or salsa.

title: foolproof meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add Marshmallow Creme, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie filling, sealing to edge of crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Cool.
Covers 9-inch pie.

title: maple dessert
directions: First Layer:
Crush vanilla wafers 1/4-inch thick or the graham crackers with a little melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stick in oven for about 5 minutes to make sure it hardens.

title: mexi-chile dip
directions: Combine
green	chiles, onion, oil and garlic salt in a small bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to vegetable mixture. Chill at least 2
hours
before
serving.	Serve with corn chips.

title: hamburger onion pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix Bisquick and cream with a fork.
Knead gently 10 times on surface lightly dusted with Bisquick.
Roll dough into a circle to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Ease dough into pan and fork edges.
Saute beef and onions until meat has lost color. Add salt, pepper, flavor extender and 2 tablespoons Bisquick. Spread in dough lined pie pan.
Beat eggs slightly and blend with cottage cheese.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: banana 'n walnut lite delight
directions: Toss bananas with lemon juice.
Layer fresh fruit, yogurt, bananas and walnuts into 4 parfait cups.
Top with additional chopped walnuts and banana slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fudge cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa; gradually stir in milk.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add small amount of mixture to egg yolks.
Return all to pan.
Cook and stir until very thick.
Remove from heat, stir in butter and vanilla. Cool 5 minutes.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown in 350° oven.

title: hamburger casserole with corn bread
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter. Add seasoning and tomatoes. Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes, then add kidney beans. Pour meat mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with corn bread batter, spreading carefully with wet knife. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt margarine and cook celery and onion until clear.
Mix all ingredients and put in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice balls
directions: Make rice balls with wet, warm hands.
Mix cooked rice with grated cheese and egg yolk.
Form ball; poke some pepperoni and Mozzarella inside ball.
When all are done, roll in beaten egg white, then in bread crumbs.
Balls should be about 2 inches in size.
Let them set in freezer for 1/2 hour; they must be firm. Fry in oil in small shallow pan until brown.
Do a few at a time. Yields about 12 balls.
Reheat in oven when ready to serve.

title: sesame-ginger chicken
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Place chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; flatten to 1/4-inch thick, using a rolling pin or meat mallet.
Use cooking spray and coat grill.
Place chicken on grill over medium hot coals.
Cook 4 minutes on each side, basting frequently with soy sauce mixture.
Garnish with green onion.

title: grandma's meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix with hands.
Messy but good.
Then press in a loaf shape.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes on broiler pan to let extra fat fall through.
Before putting in oven, use knife to make lines across the top to help fat drain. Serves 4 to 6.

title: surprise coconut pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat together eggs, milk, vanilla, flour and margarine until well combined and fold in coconut.
Pour into 2 greased (9-inch) pie pans. Bake in oven (not preheated) at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Crust forms as pie bakes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar.
Add lemon rind, eggs and milk.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and add to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar with lemon juice and drizzle over bread while it is warm.
Recipe can be doubled.
Freezes well.

title: quick roquefort dressing
directions: Combine French dressing and cheese in jar.
Shake well and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Blend vinegar, egg and water.
Stir in flour until it forms a ball. Chill 15 minutes and then divide into fourths.
Makes four 9-inch crusts.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter and saute onions and garlic until soft.
Add curry powder, salt, coriander and red pepper. Cook 1 minute.
Add broth.
Boil gently, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and half and half. Cook 5 minutes, but do not boil.
Pour into blender and blend until creamy. Serve warm. This can be made a day ahead and reheated.
Garnish with a dollop of sour cream and chopped chives.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Peel and dice onions.
Put in heavy pan with margarine.
Cook until onions are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add flour, salt, pepper, nutmeg and broth.
Cook until onions are a thickened sauce, approximately 5 minutes.
Pour into shallow casserole.
Add bread crumbs.
Layer with Swiss cheese and sprinkle Parmesan over this.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together; top with crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: garden skillet
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in large skillet with basil until tender. Add remaining ingredients. Heat until cheese melts.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine in unsalted water; drain and rinse.
Chop vegetables.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: *hamburg stuffing(for chicken or turkey)
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter until soft.
Add hamburg and saute until cooked. Add chopped walnuts, rice and parsley and cook until rice is done, 15 to 20 minutes.
Season to taste. Stuff turkey or serve as a side dish.
Pour drippings or gravy before serving.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and soda.
Add sour cream and flavoring.
Bake at 250° to 350°.
(If your stove gets very hot, use a tube pan.)

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Mix cherries, sugar and cornstarch; cook until thick, stirring constantly. Set aside to cool; mix and cook pineapple same as cherries. When cherries and pineapple are cool, mix together; add oranges, bananas and nuts. Pour into baked pie shells; sprinkle coconut on top and serve with whipped cream. (Oranges may be omitted.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered casserole at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine melted margarine and crumbs with a fork and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs at high speed for 4 minutes.
Add sifted powdered sugar and softened margarine to eggs; beat 5 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Chill 30 minutes.
Spread pineapple, then sliced bananas.
Spread whipped topping and sprinkle on pecans.
Chill 6 hours.
When ready to serve, garnish with cherries.

title: peanut fudge sauce
directions: Stir
chocolate
syrup	into peanut butter. Serve sauce over vanilla
or chocolate ice cream.
Serve with crisp cookies.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter.
Put 2/3 mixture in bottom of pan.
Mix ice cream, pudding mix and milk together. Pour into pan. Spread on Cool Whip. Sprinkle rest of crumb mix over Cool Whip, then top with candy bars.
Put in freezer until firm.

title: easy asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Place half in bowl.
Cover with half the soup.
Cover with layer of eggs.
Repeat.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: date cookies
directions: Combine
all ingredients except nuts and Rice Krispies. Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
This will burn easily. Remove from
heat	and
pour
in Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons into coconut and roll into a ball or make a log and slice when cool.

title: grape slush
directions: Blend ingredients together in a blender.
This slush has only 55 calories per serving.
Makes 1 serving.

title: divinity
directions: Heat sugar, corn syrup and water over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Cook, without stirring, until it reaches 260° or until it forms a hard ball.
In mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Continue beating whites while pouring hot syrup in. Add vanilla and beat until mixture holds shape.
Fold in nuts. Spoon on wax paper to set.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: 1 quart fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; stir in sugar 1 cup at a time.
Add salt.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook until smooth.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add onion and saute.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine all ingredients; place in baking dish. Bake at 300° to 325° for about 1 hour.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Put walnuts, raisins, currants, water, cinnamon, cloves and butter in large saucepan; boil 5 minutes.
Take from stove.
Add baking soda; this will foam to fill a gallon pan.
Watch it. Cool.
Add flour; mix well.
Bake in pan with greased brown paper on bottom.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until straw comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine first 3 ingredients with a wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by tablespoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: chili skillet
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook beef, onion, pepper and garlic until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain fat.
Add tomato juice, kidney beans, chili powder, oregano, salt and rice; cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in corn and olives; cover and cook 5 minutes more. Sprinkle with cheese; cover and cook only until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: hamburger and soup casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
At the last 10 minutes, sprinkle Chinese noodles on top.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in enough water to cover for about 10 minutes, or until almost tender.
Drain.
Mix the next 5 ingredients with potatoes; pour into a greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Just before serving, toss cracker crumbs with the melted margarine and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Top with bacon bits.
Brown under broiler.

title: betty's icicle pickles
directions: Mix lime and 2 gallons of water; soak cucumbers in solution for 24 hours. Drain and rinse well. Soak 2 to 3 hours more in plain water; drain. Make a syrup of sugar, apple cider vinegar, and celery seed; bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers. Let stand 12 hours. Add pickling spice, a few cloves, cinnamon sticks and salt. Boil 20 minutes. Pack in jars and seal. Wonderful!

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack fresh-picked cucumbers in glass jars with a layer of dill and a few pieces of garlic.
Boil water, cider vinegar, salt and alum.
Pour boiling water over cucumbers and seal.
Makes about 2 pints.

title: fancy egg scramble
directions: In large skillet cook meat and onion in 3 tablespoons of butter until onion is tender.
Add eggs and scramble just until set.
Fold mushrooms and cooked eggs into Cheese Sauce.
Turn into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
In large bowl, beat egg yolks and brown sugar until mixture is light and thickened.
Blend in peanut butter and corn syrup.
Gradually beat in milk and vanilla.
Fold
egg whites into peanut butter mixture.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Serve warm or cold. Store in refrigerator.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Set aside.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Arrange on greased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust, sealing perforations completely.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese and set aside.

title: jello salad
directions: Let jello start to congeal, then add other ingredients and totally congeal.

title: parmesan corn chowder
directions: In a Dutch oven, stir together 2 cups water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onions and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
In a large saucepan, melt the butter. Stir in flour; add milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until the mixture is thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Carefully add the cheese mixture to vegetable mixture. Stir in corn.
Heat.
DO NOT BOIL.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit-on-a-pick
directions: Cut bananas into 8 (1-inch) pieces.
Add pineapple juice and toss gently.
Drain.
Alternate fruit on 8 wooden skewers.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Place in large kettle and cook 45 minutes.
Have 3 bowls ready.
Put flour with salt and pepper in one, eggs beaten with a little milk in the second and breads crumbs in third for coating.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing.
Refrigerate overnight in a covered pan.
Approximately 1 1/2 hours before serving, drain dressing from chicken, reserving 1 cup of the marinade.
Mix reserved marinade with apricot preserves and spread over chicken in pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until nicely browned. It is not necessary to baste.
This is a very easy and delicious dish.
Serve it with rice, a green salad and crusty French bread and you have a quick dinner.

title: chicken hawaiian-style
directions: Cut chicken cutlets into bite size pieces; flour, then dip into beaten egg and garlic powder mixture.
Brown in frypan until golden brown; set aside.

title: jello cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Press flat with glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: baked fish in foil
directions: Brush fish with lemon juice and dill.
Place fish on large piece of foil.
Place onions on fish, potatoes around fish. Sprinkle carrots over potatoes, the corn over onions and fish. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook each vegetable separately until done according to directions.
Put in dish layered, first cauliflower, second Brussels sprouts, third broccoli.
Repeat.
Mix Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup and pour over the layered vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, or bake in microwave.

title: raisin-oatmeal carrot cookies
directions: Mix butter, both sugars and eggs together.
Beat, then add honey and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, allspice, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to butter mixture.
Mix well; add oats, raisins, carrots and pecans.

title: applesauce walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan or tube pan. Combine cake mix, eggs, applesauce, butter and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 25 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: elephant ears
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Mix flour, 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and salt; cut in butter.
Combine milk, egg yolk and softened yeast. Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Chill, covered, until firm enough to handle (at least 2 hours).
Turn dough onto a lightly floured board.
Punch down.
Cover with a cloth and allow to rest 10 minutes.
Roll into a rectangle (10 x 18-inches) and spread with soft butter.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon and sprinkle evenly over dough.
Roll as for jelly roll, sealing edge. The roll should be 18 inches long.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon on a large square of waxed paper. Place slices, one at a time on sugar mixture.
Roll into 5-inch rounds.
Sprinkle nuts on top and press gently.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with about 2 teaspoons sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake immediately in 400° oven for about 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield:

title: quick rich corn casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the first 5 ingredients. Add corn muffin mix. Stir well. Put batter in a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain
water
from
beans.
Combine beans, soup and 1/2 fried onion
rings and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for
15 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining onions over top.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sherbet polka dot dessert
directions: Make ice cream balls out of sherbets and freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Soften chocolate chip ice cream and beat until fluffy.
Layer sherbet balls in chilled tube pan, alternating colors of sherbet.
Pour in chocolate chip ice cream as you layer to fill in, adding more sherbet and more ice cream until all is used.
Freeze at least 12 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Make mixture of first 3 ingredients. Cut each biscuit into quarters. Roll each biscuit quarter in sugar mixture and drop into Bundt cake pan. Pour remaining sugar over the top and sprinkle with the nuts. Melt the oleo and pour over the top of the biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Pour glaze over top of cake after you remove it from pan while cake is still hot.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix all together until light and fluffy.
Drop by spoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Layer, starting with 1st ingredient and refrigerate.

title: goulash
directions: Place 10 pound ham, sliced and tied (optional) into deep roaster pan.
Pour 1 cup Coca-Cola over ham, slowly.
Put lid on pan and bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: pots de creme
directions: In blender, add eggs, milk and condensed milk.
Blend very well.
Take sugar, put in saucepan over medium heat; caramelize sugar and pour into Pyrex custard cups.
This will harden rapidly. Pour blended ingredients into custard cups.
Set custard cups into a heatproof dish; add water up to 1/2 of custard cups.
Cover with aluminum.
Cook at 325° for 2 hours or until knife inserted comes clean.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, loosen edges with knife and invert onto dessert plate.

title: chocolate unusual method cake
directions: Mix together sugar and sifted flour in a large bowl.
Combine butter, cocoa and water in pot and cook to boiling point.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour and sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add buttermilk, sour cream or sour milk.
Add slightly beaten eggs, vanilla and baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Prepare icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Take out of freezer 30 minutes before serving to thaw.

title: vidalia's omelet
directions: Melt 2 tbsp. butter in non-stick small skillet.
When it starts to crackle, add chopped onion.
toss frequently to caramelize (ever so slightly burn) outside of onion pieces.
Set aside.
While 1 tbsp butter is melting in same skillet, crack two eggs in bowl.
Add 1/4 cup sour cream: Stir just enough to blend well.
Pour egg mixture into pan.
Allow to cook about 30 seconds.
Stir from bottom with spatula.
Allow to continue cooking about 45 seconds more.
Use half of cheese and half of onion to make a line down the middle of the circle.
Continue cooking until cheese starts to melt.
Lift pan from heat and shake back and forth to be sure it is loosened from the pan.
Then with a flip of the wrist, fold it in half and slide onto plate. Sprinkle with pepper and basil.
Serves 2.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a bowl; mix well.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Slowly add milk, tossing mixture with a fork just until it holds together.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water 4 minutes.
Drain.
Put in baking dish.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over vegetables. Sprinkle
with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Top with onions, bake 10 minutes more.

title: cherry-pineapple cake
directions: Place can of cherry pie filling in bottom of large loaf pan. Pour can of pineapple over cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Cut butter in small squares and place over all cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over entire mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: quick delicious rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together about 2 minutes.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange-walnut fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with foil so it extends over the edges of pan. Butter the foil; set pan aside.

title: best pie crust
directions: Mix, roll
and	bake as you normally would any fine pie pastry.
Yields 6 (8-inch) pie crusts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together in food processor.
Mix into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley that have been mixed together.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and let stand a day or more.
Use pudding mix dry.

title: salt clay
directions: Combine all ingredients, except food coloring, in a saucepan and cook, over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens into a dough mass.
Remove from heat immediately and cool until you can handle, but still warm.
Place on wax paper and knead like bread.

title: caesar potato salad(servings:  4)
directions: In blender, mix together egg, Italian dressing, cheese, sauce, mustard and salt until well blended.
Add to potatoes in a bowl and toss to mix well.
Refrigerate to chill.
May garnish with olives.
Makes 8 servings; 8 calories each without olive garnish. Suggested Wine: Chardonnay.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk. Add nuts, raisins and dates.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat shortening in 1 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted; remove from heat.
Mix in brown sugar, vanilla and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.
Makes about 16 brownies.

title: baked alaska
directions: Place individual sponge cake cups or pieces of cake on a board. Fill the center of each with a scoop of flavored ice cream.
Place in freezer while preparing Special Meringue.
Beat 6 large egg whites with 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar until frothy.
Beat in gradually, 1 cup sugar.
Continue beating until meringue is stiff and glossy.
Cover cake and ice cream with Special Meringue, sealing meringue to board.

title: clam fritters
directions: Grind clams.
Put crackers in blender, using high speed.
Pour crumbs into clams.
Add beaten eggs.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add Tabasco sauce and lemon juice.
Let sit 20 minutes. Heat skillet with 1/2-inch oil.
If mixture is too thin, add more cracker crumbs.
Fry to golden brown.
(Mixture should be like a soft cookie dough.)

title: gazpacho dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except garlic salt, salt and pepper. Add garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Dip tortilla chips.

title: welcome punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix together chilled pineapple pink grapefruit juice, pineapple juice, apricot nectar and club soda. Add ice ring and garnish with mint sprigs.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover filling with pie dough.
Roll edges under; flute.
Cut slits in center to allow steam to escape. Cook, uncovered, in 425° oven until crust is brown, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: In a saucepan melt margarine.
Add peanut butter and heat until smooth.
Add brown sugar and lightly beaten eggs, flour and vanilla.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat brown and granulated sugars, shortening, egg, vanilla and milk until smooth.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add all at once to egg mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add oats and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Yields 3 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: orange fuzzy jello
directions: Add hot water to jello and stir well.
Add pudding and Cool Whip and mix (use a whisk or fork).
Add mandarin oranges.
(Okay to use juice also if they are Dole.)
Chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Sift flour into a large bowl.
Beat eggs and add with rest of ingredients to the flour in large bowl.
Mix well, making sure all the zucchini and flour is mixed into the batter.
Keep mixing for several minutes.
Pour into greased pans and bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool in pans on cookie racks and store in plastic wrap in freezer, if desired.
Freezes well.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
allow to set overnight to mix flavors. If desired, you may
marinate chicken with the sauce one night prior to barbecuing.
For best taste,
place
chicken on a rack over an open pit and barbecue
slowly
(approximately
3 hours).
Turn chicken and baste with sauce each time
chicken
is turned.
Chicken is done when the leg bone turns freely in its joint and the barbecue sauce is depleted.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Divide cake in half.
Break 1/2 cake in small pieces.
Place in punch bowl.
Mix 2 boxes vanilla instant pudding as directed on box.
Pour half over cake in punch bowl.
Slice 3 bananas.
Layer over pudding.
Drain 1 can of pineapple.
Layer over bananas.
Put 1 can cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Break the other half cake in small pieces.
Place on top of pie filling.
Then layer pudding, bananas, pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
This will fill a large punch bowl.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Coat nuts in mixture of other ingredients.
Melt 1 stick of butter in cookie sheet.
Spread nuts in pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until butter is absorbed.
Turn every 15 minutes.

title: ham and shrimp casserole
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in a saucepan and add onions.
Cook on low heat until onions are soft.
Turn off heat; sprinkle in flour and mix well.
Gradually stir in milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Return to the heat and cook until sauce thickens.
Set aside.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk. Bring to a boil and then quickly mix in the oatmeal, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered waxed paper or buttered countertop and let cool.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Prepare pistachio pudding according to box instructions.
Add the undrained pineapple, chopped nuts and miniature marshmallows. Stir and add Cool Whip and coconut.
Chill and serve.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies; let cool. Prick holes in top of brownies with fork.
Pour coffee liqueur over the brownies; set aside.
Prepare mousse. Break candy bars by tapping with a hammer.
Break up brownies in small pieces.
Place half of the brownies in bottom of a large glass bowl. Cover with half of the mousse, then half the candy and half whipped topping. Repeat layers.

title: dirty pudding
directions: Cream the cheese and Cool Whip.
Add powder pudding and beat. Add approximately 1/2 the milk called for on the pudding box (if too thick, add a bit more milk).
Add 1/2 of the cookies, crushed. Garnish with the remaining 1/2 of cookies, whole or crushed.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Put in ice cream freezer and fill to the line with Orange Crush.
Freeze according to your freezer directions.
You can use crushed strawberries and strawberry crush.

title: swedish fruit soup(fruktsoppa)
directions: Rinse well in cold water.
With a sharp knife, remove pits from prunes.
Put fruits into large saucepot with tight-fitting cover.
Add 2 quarts water.
Cover and soak fruits for 2 to 3 hours.
Then add 1/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons tapioca, 3-inch piece stick cinnamon and 1 teaspoon grated orange peel.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer about 1 hour or until fruit is tender.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 cup red raspberry fruit syrup.
Chill soup in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream and (optional) slivered blanched almonds.
Recipe can be made without raisins.
Makes about 3 quarts soup.

title: cinnamon-pear crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel and slice pears.
Toss with next 4 ingredients.
In a food processor, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and egg.
Place pears in 9-inch square baking dish.
Cover with topping and drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until fruit is cooked and crust is golden brown.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat, skim off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: piquanties
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients with cheese.
Season with parsley and chives to taste.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in ground nutmeats mixed with chopped parsley.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and flour; add a little milk to make a paste.
Add rest of milk, egg yolks and salt.
Stir while cooking until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Mix peanut butter with enough powdered sugar to make a crumbly mixture.
Put in bottom of baked pie shell.
(Save a little to sprinkle on meringue.)
Pour filling in crust; top with meringue, made by beating egg whites and gradually adding 6 tablespoons sugar, beating until stiff.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and brown in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy no-bake choco-oat cookies
directions: Measure into saucepan the first 5 ingredients.
Stir constantly until mixture reaches a boil (about 3 minutes).
Put oatmeal and vanilla into bowl; stir these ingredients and add other ingredients from saucepan.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and let cool.

title: frozen kahlua cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add cocoa and egg yolks.
Dissolve soda and water and combine with coffee and 1/2 cup Kahlua.
Add to batter alternating with flour. Add vanilla and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter in pan.
Run knife through batter to remove air bubbles.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Combine confectioners sugar and 1/2 of Kahlua.
Pour over warm cake; cover with foil and freeze.

title: mock whipped cream
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Turn the mixer at low speed; as blending takes place, increase speed to high.
Whip 5 to 8 minutes or until whipped cream consistency.

title: taco casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese; return to oven to melt cheese.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a pie plate.
Cook vegetables for 5 minutes in boiling water, then drain (or cook 2 minutes in microwave).
Mix vegetables, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, about 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater. Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: lazy luscious lemon cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in sugar and lemon juice. Pour into baked shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until slightly firm.
Chill.
Whip cream with powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on pie before serving.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place uncooked beef into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle onion on top and pour undiluted soup over this.
Layer Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: choc oatmeal no bake cookies
directions: Melt
margarine;
add
milk
and sugar.
Bring to boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Then add cocoa, oatmeal and peanut butter and
mix well.
Then immediately put out heaping teaspoonfuls out on cookie sheet.
Let it get hard.

title: raita
directions: Mix all the ingredients, being careful not to crush the banana.
If the raita is prepared hours before the dinner, reserve the banana until just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: orange summer salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple.
Bring to a good boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from fire and add jello.
Mix well and let cool slightly.
Then stir in jello.
Then stir or fold in Cool Whip Lite.
Then pour in mold.
Other flavors can be used. Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: fruit cocktail coffee cake
directions: Mix in a bowl sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, egg and fruit cocktail.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch pan* (greased).

title: no work dinner
directions: Mix ingredients and use a 2 qt.
covered casserole dish. Bake in oven with a lid on dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove lid and sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato paste and two or three cans of water.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and simmer about 10 minutes.
Remove and add cottage cheese and mushrooms.
Boil noodles, drain, coat in butter.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with noodles, sauce and cheese.
Repeat.
Top with Parmesan cheese and the parsley.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine all ingredients; shape into long roll.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until hard.
Slice 1/4-inch and place fairly far apart on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle a few caraway seeds in center of each wafer.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot or cold. Makes 150 to 170.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix crushed pineapple (with juice) and cherry pie filling. Spread in a well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Mix coconut and pecans; sprinkle over mixture.
Slice margarine sticks evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
May need to cover at mid-point; coconut may burn.

title: soda cracker bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line a 15 x 10 cookie sheet with foil. Spray with Pam.
Put one layer of soda crackers on foil.
Mix sugar and butter in a saucepan; boil for 3 minutes only.
Pour over crackers.
Bake 5 minutes or until crackers float and bubble. Remove from oven and sprinkle with chips, then nuts.
Cut into squares while warm.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: mexican red sauce
directions: Saute in oil the onions and garlic until soft.
Add mashed tomatoes and paste, pepper and seasonings.
Heat to boil.
Simmer 20 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with chips.
Hot!

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix butter, flour and 1 tablespoon sugar as for pie crust. Press mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Watch, as it burns easily! Cool.
Beat softened cream cheese and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy.
Fold in beaten cream or Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Spread blueberries over cheese mixture and chill several hours.
Cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water.
In a large bowl, combine pasta and remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours (or over night) to blend flavors.
Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook and stir ground beef until browned; drain.
Stir in chili beans, tomato sauce, taco sauce, chili powder and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Arrange coarsely broken corn chips in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with beef mixture; spread with sour cream.
Top with onion, tomato and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot and bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.
Arrange additional tortilla chips around edge of casserole.
Serve with garnishes of shredded lettuce and taco sauce, if desired.
Makes 16 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients
and cook in a 9 x 13-inch dish for 25 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: edible play dough
directions: Put peanut butter in bowl.
Pour in honey; add some powdered milk.
Mix with hands.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut the ribs in sizes to serve.
Season with salt and pepper. Brown in pan on top of stove.

title: pizza biscuits
directions: Mix biscuit as directed and add above ingredients. Bake as directed on Bisquick box.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine the cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar, mixing until smooth.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and chopped pecans.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Add sugar and peanut butter.
Gradually add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell. Crush peanuts and sprinkle over top.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) cake pans or 3 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: easter egg candy (buckeyes)
directions: Melt oleo and cool a bit.
Add other ingredients as listed. Roll into balls or desired shapes.
Place on cookie sheets.
Cool 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Melt 18 oz Hershey bars.
Put toothpick into balls or shapes to dip in melted chocolate.
Put back on cookie sheets lined with wax paper.
Place back in refrigerator until firm.
Makes about 140 1-inch balls or 90 small eggs (1x2).

title: fettuccine rene
directions: Cook fettuccine and drain.
In saucepan, saute shallots in butter, stir in chicken broth and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove pan from heat and gradually stir in cream.
Add pasta, sour cream, Parmesan and chives; toss and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter or margarine together until light and
fluffy.
Add sugar and cream until smooth.
Add egg and
beat well.
Beat
in peanut butter and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Roll dough into balls
about
1 inch
in
diameter.
Place
on greased cookie sheets and
