flatten by pressing with tip of teaspoon.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put a layer of coconut and pecans in pan.
Prepare cake mix as per directions.
Pour over coconut, pecan layer.
Mix softened oleo and cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla; spread over batter.
(I drop by spoonful.)
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: veal marengo
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a shallow bowl, blend the flour, salt and pepper. Dredge veal in mix.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Add veal.
Brown on all sides, 5 to 7 minutes.
Transfer to casserole.
Add remaining oil, onion and garlic to skillet.
Saute, stirring over medium heat, until the onion is soft, about 5 minutes.
Add wine, water, tomato paste, thyme, tarragon and orange peel. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Pour the mixture over the veal. Cover and bake for 2 hours.
Add mushrooms.
Re-cover and bake 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned chocolate pudding
directions: Scald milk; mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch by sifting.
Beat egg yolks with a fork; add about 1/2 cup scalded milk to yolks, then add mixture back to rest of milk.
Slowly mix milk with sifted ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter (or margarine) and vanilla.

title: squash casserole(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Boil onion and squash until tender; drain and mash. Mix well with all other ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: pine bark candy
directions: Line large pan with sides with aluminum foil.
On top of this, line saltines.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cobbler
directions: Combine in saucepan:
rhubarb pieces, 1 1/2 cups sugar, tapioca, 1/8 teaspoon salt and cinnamon.
Wait 5 minutes, then add strawberries (thawed).
Bring mixture to boiling.
Cook until thick, about 6 minutes.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.

title: spinach and tomato salad
directions: Wash spinach; drain.
Combine oil and vinegar in mixer bowl; beat for 3 to 5 minutes or until well blended.
Add sugar, onion, catsup, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Beat well.
Combine spinach, eggs, tomato and bacon in large bowl.
Add desired amount of dressing; toss to mix.
Dressing will keep well in refrigerator. Yield:
6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put in casserole.
Mix mayonnaise, onions, soup, egg and milk.
Stir well.
Lay sliced cheese on top. Dot with butter.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: trash bag taco salad
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning and prepare according to package directions.
Cool.
Toss with remaining ingredients in a large plastic bag or container.
Makes 40 to 50 servings.

title: lean french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt and 4 1/2 cups flour, stirring well.
Add flour to form a heavy mass.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead in remainder of flour until dough is smooth, satiny and elastic.
Place dough in lightly oiled bowl.
Turn to cover all surfaces.
Cover; let rise to double (2 to 3 hours).
Combine cornstarch and boiling water.
Cool.
Punch down dough and turn onto work surface.
Divide dough into 4. Roll each 12 to 13-inches and 1-inch in diameter.
Place on connmealed baking sheet or lightly greased French bread forms.
Slash dough diagonally 3 times.
Cover, rise until almost double.
Brush with cornstarch mixture.
Put loaves in preheated 425° oven.
Brush with cornstarch mixture 2 to 3 times during first 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until sounds hollow.

title: hollandaise sauce(zero cholesterol)
directions: Put egg substitute, lemon juice and pepper into blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour margarine into mixture and blend together until sauce is slightly thickened.
Put into microwave for 20 seconds to thicken more.
Contains 35 calories per tablespoon.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: Combine caramels, 1/3 cup milk and melt in double boiler or in microwave.
Combine cake mix and remaining 1/3 of milk and butter and stir in nuts.
Place 1/2 cake mixture in greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle on chocolate chips and top with caramel, spoon rest of dough on top. Bake again 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sharp cheddar spread
directions: Combine cold pack cheese food, softened cream cheese and margarine.
Mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Mold into an empty 1 pound margarine tub or suitable container coated with additional margarine.
Chill until firm. Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: luncheon buns
directions: Combine ingredients and let dough rise 45 min.
Use butter and cornmeal to coat buns.
Cut top of buns when they have risen 1/2 an hour.
Let rise a little longer, then bake at 400°F until nicely browned.

title: peppered rib-eye steaks
directions: Brush steaks lightly with olive oil.
In a small bowl, mix all seasonings.
Sprinkle seasonings over steaks and press into both sides.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Grill steaks, turning once, over medium hot coals 14 to 18 minutes for rare and 24 to 28 minutes for well done.

title: sesame chicken salad
directions: In a bowl, combine chicken, celery, pineapple chunks, mayonnaise, 2 teaspoons sesame seed, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Toss well.
Arrange lettuce leaves on serving dish and top with chicken salad; sprinkle with remaining sesame seed and pineapple juice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread. Add pepper, onion, celery, dressing, beans and tomato. Sprinkle top with bacon bits.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together.
May spread flour on outside to make it easier to roll out and cut.
Melt 1/2 stick of oleo in a baking pan.
Cover with 1/2 stick melted oleo.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: parmesan fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler pan.
Cook very slowly over low heat, stirring constantly, until all is melted. Pour into a fondue pot and keep warm.
Serve with French bread, cut into little squares.
Just enjoy.

title: chili dip
directions: Melt cream cheese over low heat.
Add soup and chilies.
Cook until well heated.
Serve with chips.

title: mounds
directions: Mix coconut, margarine, powdered sugar and Eagle Brand milk well.
Shape into balls or squares.
Chill for 20 minutes in freezer.
Melt paraffin and milk chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in mixture and place on wax paper to cool.

title: raspberry-mandarin tartlets
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together flour and sugar.
Using a pastry blender, cut in the butter until pieces are the size of small peas.

title: cajun macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Grease a large casserole dish with margarine.
Beat eggs and milk.
Grate cheese.
Layer macaroni and cheese and butter. Add egg mixture; mix.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Grease shallow, 2-quart baking dish.
Mix in Veg-All and chicken.
Mix broth with pepper and soup.
Pour over Veg-All and chicken.
Combine flour, milk and butter.
Stir until smooth. Pour over chicken.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: sunday scrambled eggs
directions: Fry onions.
Place in a bowl and mix in all other ingredients.
Beat mixture lightly enough to thoroughly mix.
In a frying pan, coated with cooking spray, heat to medium high and add the egg mixture.
Cook while stirring often to scramble and continue until the eggs attain a degree of dryness that you enjoy most.
Serve with buttered toast.
Bacon optional.

title: orange pineapple bavarian(from 1975 edition)
directions: *Diet jello may be used for less calories.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 3 tablespoons warm water.
Combine sugar, butter, 1 cup water, salt and eggs.
Add yeast and flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough in 2 circles.
Spread with butter.
Cut into 16 triangles.
Roll each beginning with wide end.
Place individual horns on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: "knife and fork" soup
directions: In a 4 to 6 quart Dutch oven combine sausage, carrots, celery, onion soup mix, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water; stir.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Mix in tomatoes, breaking up; add hash browns, okra, oregano and hot pepper sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir once or twice.
Ladle the thick soup into large soup bowls.
Serve with crusty bread and mustard.

title: grandma maul's christmas cookies(austrian-hungarian)
directions: Mix all together. I use small cookie cutters as these are pretty rich.
Extra touches, prior to baking, paint with egg white and dip in sugar, walnut mixture and bake.
Bake at approximately 350° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: dilled sour cream and cucumber
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cucumbers, dill weed, salt, pepper, sugar, red wine vinegar, parsley, onions and sour cream. Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Turn the mixture into a serving dish.
Garnish with tomato wedges and parsley.

title: san clemente curry
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter with curry powder and salt; add chopped tomato and onion.
Cook until soft.
Add lemon juice, shrimp and sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Cut avocados in halves, remove seeds and skin and fill centers with the hot curry. Arrange on lettuce leaf.
May be served with rice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place peeled, sliced apples in a 2-quart or 11 x 7-inch casserole dish.
Blend together with a pastry blender until crumbly the butter, brown sugar and margarine.
Sprinkle over the apple slices.
If apples are dry, add water before you put on the sugar mixture.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° about 35 to 45 minutes.
Test apples for doneness at 35 minutes.
May be served with lemon sauce, whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cocktail snacks
directions: Mix the last three ingredients, add crackers and stir until evenly coated.
Place in screw type jar.
Store in refrigerator. They keep forever.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix like cake.
Add oats, chocolate chips and nuts last.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes.
I use a sheet cake pan.
You can use a cookie sheet.
Put strips of foil on edge to prevent bars from getting too brown.
Putting a small pan of water on bottom of oven helps to keep the cookies from getting too brown.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain well. Meanwhile, for sauce, in a medium saucepan, combine water, mushrooms, frozen green beans, green or red pepper, garlic, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Do not drain.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, cook celery and onion in butter until tender; add remaining ingredients except noodles and parsley. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf; add noodles and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes longer or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: hot seafood dip
directions: Drain crabmeat and shrimp.
Combine all ingredients, except grated cheese.
Mix.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: mammaw's skillet molasses cake
directions: Mix sugar and molasses with mixer.
Add flour with soda and spices.
Add egg and then hot water; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 325° until it springs back when touched.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Soak cookies in milk and drain milk out (just like dipping to eat). Put 1 layer of cookies in bottom of Corning-ware or glass pie pan, then a layer of Cool Whip.
Continue to layer in this order until pan is as full as you want it ending with Cool Whip topping.
Cover with crushed cookies.
Store in fridge.

title: hamburger dinner
directions: Season ground beef.
Make into 5 or 6 hamburger patties. Place slice of potato, slice of onion, slice of green pepper and a slice of tomato on each side of meat patty.
Wrap each patty with vegetables in foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot. Yields 5 or 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange; add sugar and let stand. Dissolve jello in water.
Chill until partially set.
Add to cranberry mixture; add nuts, marshmallows, apples and pineapple. Pour into mold.
Chill until firm or overnight.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 4 to 6 people. Great with vegetables.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Mix salt, flour and sour cream.
Add soup and wine.
Cover chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 90 minutes.

title: basic muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift dry ingredients together in bowl. In separate bowl, mix egg, milk, sugar and oil.
Make a "well" in dry ingredients and add liquid all at once.
Stir just enough to dampen all the flour.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, bring beans and 2 quarts of water to a boil.
Boil briskly 2 minutes, then remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 1 hour.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven, heat oil and saute onions, celery, carrot and garlic until soft, but not browned.
Add remaining 1 quart of water, parsley, cayenne pepper, cloves, mustard and beans (with their liquid).
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer for about 3 hours.
Place about half of the beans with about 1 cup of the liquid from the soup in a blender or food processor; process until smooth.
Return puree to Dutch oven.
Reheat soup over medium heat.
Stir in sherry. Garnish with nonfat plain yogurt and cilantro.
Makes eight 1-cup servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cover with grated cheese and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: crab-stuffed potato
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Split in half lengthwise, scoop out and reserve shells.
In bowl, mash potatoes with butter, milk, onion and salt until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Stir in grated cheese and crab meat.
Fill shells with mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: "bill cosby" beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, combine beans, corn, bacon, onion, peppers, barbecue sauce, chili powder and garlic powder.
Cover and cook over medium heat 35 minutes.
Stir often.
Just before serving, top with cheese and pepper rings.

title: u.m.w.'s apple and date pudding for "350"
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; let stand until cool.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and blend.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Add apples and nuts.
Add dates from which liquid has been drained.
Pour into 4 greased 7 x 11-inch pans (waxed paper in bottom) or use 35 to 36 pans for larger recipe.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cut servings approximately 2 x 5 inches.
Serve with Brown Sugar Sauce.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and pour into paper-lined muffin tins. Freeze.
Remove from tins and place in freezer bags.
Return to freezer or serve.
Makes 12.

title: creamed celery parmesan
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet until frothy. Add 1 cup slivered almonds and 3 cups diced celery.
Cover; saute for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 2 more tablespoons butter and let melt.
Blend in 2 tablespoons flour and cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup light cream, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1 cup boiling chicken broth.
Stir until blended.
Cook over moderately high heat, stirring until sauce comes to a boil and thickens.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole and sprinkle with 3 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese.
Broil until the cheese browns.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel penuche (microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave 7 minutes on High, stirring after 2 minutes.
Add caramels.
Microwave 45 seconds; remove, beat vigorously until mixture is smooth.
Add nuts. Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 cups evaporated milk and bring to a boil.
Add 30 large marshmallows and stir until smooth.
Add coconut and spread on cake; cool.

title: kansas peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together until it looks like Bisquick.
Spread 1/2 the mixture in a baked pie shell.

title: red hot applesauce
directions: Put red hots in water.
Bring to a boil and stir until red hots are gone.
Add jello and mix well.
Add applesauce.
Stir and put in refrigerator.

title: mock meat balls iii
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix well.
Shape into one-inch balls.
Saute in small amount of oil.
Can be used for dipping or spaghetti.

title: almond roca
directions: You should line the bottom of pan with wax paper, otherwise this sticks to the pan.

title: tofu salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and enjoy!

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix together rhubarb and sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add 3 ounce box of jello.
Stir in thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: sausage roll
directions: Combine flour, sugar, meal, baking powder and salt.
Sift together in a large bowl.
Stir in vegetable oil.
Add milk and blend.
Add a couple of extra tablespoons of milk, if necessary, to form a stiff dough.
Roll in rectangle on a lightly floured surface.
Spread on sausage and roll jelly-roll fashion lengthwise.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill or freeze.
When ready to use, slice and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: weight watchers breakfast pie
directions: Put in blender; mix for 30 seconds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cinnamon before baking.

title: fridge cookies
directions: Mix and form into roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and leave in fridge overnight.
Slice and bake.
Set oven at 350° and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat peanut butter and butter until blended. Gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients and mix. Stir in chocolate chips and vanilla. Spread in buttered 9 x 13 pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until slightly brown.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplants and boil until tender.
Drain in colander 15 minutes.
Place eggplant in a bowl and add eggs, milk, seasonings, 1/2 cracker crumbs, 1/2 grated cheese and 1/2 melted margarine.
Pour eggplant mixture about 2 or 3 inches thick in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, cracker crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 450° until golden brown and firm (about 30 minutes).
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms. Remove stems and finely chop. Drain mushroom caps on paper towel. Melt butter in skillet. Add onion, pepperoni, green pepper, garlic and chopped mushroom stems.
Cook until tender, not brown. Add cracker crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and oregano.
Mix well. Stir in chicken broth. Spoon stuffing into caps, rounding tops.
Place caps in shallow baking dish with 1/4-inch water covering bottom of baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for about 25 minutes. Enjoy!

title: super seafood salad
directions: Cut Crab Delights in flakes.
Half in shred.
Combine with mayonnaise, celery and onions.
Serve on lettuce or as sandwich filling.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium-sized bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Form mixture into patties, approximately 3 to 4-inches in diameter and 3/4-inch thick.
Cook on top of stove in oil for 6 to 8 minutes, over medium heat or until golden brown. If patties do not stick together, more cracker crumbs may be added.

title: enchiladas
directions: To make sauce, combine and bring to boil tomato soup, tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, oil, chili powder (2 teaspoons) and garlic powder.
Set aside to cool.
Brown meat, onions, half of grated cheese and 1 cup sauce.
Set aside to cool.
Dip each tortilla in rest of sauce.
Lay in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 1/3 cup of meat mixture in each tortilla and roll up each one until pan is filled.
Pour any remaining sauce over top.
Place rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tub salad
directions: Mix together.
Put into long casserole dish and freeze. Tastes just like ice cream.
Great for people with dairy allergies.

title: grilled potatoes with broccoli
directions: Place four pieces of foil out.
Put 1/4 of potatoes on each piece.
Place 3 to 4 pieces of broccoli on top of potatoes.
Top with 3 ounces cheese and 1/4 stick butter.
Season to taste with garlic pepper and rosemary.
Pour on 2 to 3 ounces of beer.
Wrap foil.
Place on grill for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: candied fruitcake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Add pineapple, cherries and dates.
Mix well with hands to coat each piece of fruit with flour.
Beat eggs until frothy; gradually beat in sugar.
Add to fruit and mix well.
With hands, mix in pecan halves.
Grease and line with brown paper two 9-inch clamp or clampless spring-form pans; grease paper.
Divide dough into pans and press down firmly with fingers.
If necessary, rearrange fruit and nuts to fill any empty spaces.
Bake in slow oven at 275° about 1 1/4 hours.
Let cakes stand in pans about 5 minutes.
Turn out on racks and pull off brown paper.
Cool.

title: cookie dough pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in order.
Beat well on medium speed. Pour into prepared pan and bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test with knife blade in center.
Remove from pan onto plate and cool. Can be served plain or with light frosting.

title: fruit nibblers
directions: Combine rum, orange juice and extract.
Pour over fruit; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Serve with wooden picks.

title: candied dill slices
directions: Start with dill pickles purchased from any store. Note that these pickles must be kept refrigerated after treatment. Drain all juices from pickles. Slice pickles 1/4-inch thick into larger bowl. Pour in sugar and vinegar. Add spices. Let stand at room temperature. Stir occasionally (about 4 hours) until sugar dissolves. Put back in jars and seal and refrigerate. Let stand 4 days before using.

title: super cheese pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter until crumbly.
Set aside 3 tablespoons of the mixture. With the back of a spoon, press the rest of the mixture on bottom and side of well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Do not spread on rim.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together thoroughly.
Divide filling and spread evenly over tortillas.
Roll up tortillas; cover each tightly with plastic wrap, twisting ends.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Unwrap; cut in slices, 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Serve with salsa.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer.
Add chilies, green onions, olives and garlic salt.
Spread each tortilla with cream cheese mixture and roll up.
Refrigerate, covered.
When ready to serve, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Makes approximately 60 to 70 appetizers.

title: army s~o~s creamed ground beef
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Stir in flour, bouillon, salt and pepper; saute for 5 minutes or until flour is absorbed.
Gradually stir in milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring all to a simmer, stirring occasionally.
Cook until thickened, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: caramel pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well and be sure to have a good measure of flour.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: turkey ole
directions: Arrange sliced turkey over flavored rice.
Add turkey gravy, if desired.
Garnish with ripe olives.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except potato chips) in 9 x 12 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Crush potato chips on top.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes a great summertime quick meal.

title: iced green tomato pickles
directions: Soak sliced tomatoes in lime water for 24 hours; drain.
Soak in fresh water for 4 hours, changing water every half hour.
Drain well.
Make a syrup of sugar and vinegar; add spices.
Bring syrup to a boil; pour over tomatoes.
Let stand overnight.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven.
Add onion and cook until soft. Stir in paprika and cook for 2 minutes.
Add meat and cook until well browned.
Add marjoram, beef broth and 1 can of water.
Bring to a boil; lower heat, cover and simmer for 80 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice and serve.

title: twinkie cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer Twinkies, pudding, pineapple, bananas and cover with Cool Whip.
Top with pecans.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare and cook cornbread in a 9x13-inch pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and add cream of celery soup and butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick good caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter; add
brown
sugar and cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring
constantly.
Add milk and continue stirring until mixture comes
to
a
boil.
Remove
from heat and cool. Add confectioners
sugar
until you have the right consistency to spread.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate.
Dip in flour, then egg mixed with milk, then in corn meal.
Fry in Crisco at 375° until brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
(Should be size of coarse crumbs.)
Place apples in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle flour mixture over apples.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with ice cream, light cream or whipped cream.

title: flank steak oriental
directions: In baking dish, combine scallions, soy sauce, sherry or broth, oil, sugar and garlic powder.
Add steak; turn once to coat. Cover and marinate 40 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients. Remove steak from marinade.
Spread half of vegetables over entire surface of steak.
Starting with long side, roll steak jelly roll fashion with the grain.
Secure with wooden toothpick.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Combine all ingredients except onion rings with thawed hash brown potatoes.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass pan sprayed with Pam. Cook at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Put onion rings on top the last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: appalachian cherry pie recipe
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1 cup liquid.
In a large saucepan, combine 3/4 cup of the sugar and the cornstarch.
Stir in reserved cherry liquid.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir for 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining sugar, margarine and almond extract. Stir in cherries.
Cool slightly.

title: linda's spinach casserole
directions: Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: grandma's seafoam candy
directions: Boil brown sugar and water until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour over well beaten egg whites.
Add pecans and beat until candy starts to cool.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool and serve.

title: los feliz casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until almost done.
Drain and set aside.
Brown meat; add tomato sauce, green pepper, green onions and seasoning.
Cook gently for 10 minutes.
Spread half of the noodles on bottom of casserole pan; spread all of the cheese mixture over noodles.
Layer remaining noodles and then all of the meat mixture.
Cover evenly with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through and top cheese is melted and browned. Serves 8.

title: orange glazed pecans
directions: In medium saucepan, mix orange concentrate and sugar; bring to boil. Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add nuts and stir to coat. Spread nuts on foil in single layer so that nuts do not touch. Cool until glaze is firm.

title: country chicken and biscuits
directions: Boil chicken; cut into cubes.
Arrange chicken in glass baking dish; set aside.
Put soup, water and frozen vegetables over chicken.
Fry bacon.
Crumble bacon over top.
Cover with slices of cheese.
Top with rolled biscuits.
Bisquick works well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cold duck punch
directions: Mix liquids in punch bowl and add sherbet.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Dice all ingredients together including tomatoes.
Put in large pot with tomato juice and water to cover.
Add bouillon and Sweet 'N Low and cook.
Simmer over low heat 5 hours.
It is best done in crock-pot on low for 8 hours.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until slightly tender. Layer potatoes in casserole dish, then 4 slices of Velveeta, then another layer of potatoes and 4 more slices of cheese and 2 tablespoons of butter. Pour milk over top and cook in microwave until cheese and butter are melted, then serve.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix all ingredients in order listed. Drop by small spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: shrimp melts
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on toasted English muffin halves.
Bake at 350° until bubbles.
Makes 16.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour and soda and add to the butter mixture alternately with sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes (or until cake tests done).
Cool 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine baking cocoa and baking soda. Blend in 1/3 cup melted margarine.
Add boiling water and stir until well blended.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining melted margarine.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chunks.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook sweet potatoes, peel and mash while hot.
Add all ingredients.
(If mixture is dry add more orange juice.) Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and return to oven until brown.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, pecans and sugar.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Make jello with lemon Jell-O, hot water and pineapple juice.
Combine cranberry mixture, Jell-O and pineapple. Chill in large covered bowl, stirring if necessary.

title: grandma's spice cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with desired frosting.
Buttercream is best.

title: the cajun cake(has no eggs or oil)
directions: Mix and pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan (or can spray pan with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly less than instructions.
Mix broccoli, egg, mayo, onion, soup and cheese in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix stuffing with butter and sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great doubled for parties.

title: aunt elizabeth's pineapple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients; cream shortening and sugar.
To the creamed mixture; add eggs and lemon juice. Then blend in pineapple and syrup.
Add flour mixture slowly while beating.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: leisel's kahlua
directions: Boil water and dissolve the sugar.
Add instant coffee and dissolve.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add vodka and mix. Pour into 2 quart bottles.
Split vanilla bean in half and put in each bottle.
Store for 2 weeks in a dark place.
Serve over chipped ice and add milk of cream, if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, one a a time.
Add Crisco oil.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, carrots and walnuts.
Sift in flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 loaf pans at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Pour oil into large bowl. Add sugar and beaten eggs. Blend well until smooth. Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder. Gradually beat flour into first mixture, beating well. Fold in apples and pecans. Pour in a greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dilly bread
directions: Blend yeast and water and let stand until yeast is soft.
Warm cottage cheese and combine with all other ingredients.
Beat as you combine flour to make dough stiff.
Let rise 50 to 60 minutes. Punch down.
Turn onto a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Serve while hot.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter apple crumble
directions: Measure flour and 1 cup of sugar into mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine and peanut butter until crumbs resemble coarse meal. Pare and slice apples.
Arrange in 2-quart casserole or shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with the remaining sugar, orange rind, orange juice and water.
Cover with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender, about 45 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with ice cream.
Makes 10 servings.

title: beef roast
directions: Take sharp fork and stick holes in the roast.
Rub roast with salt and pepper, minced garlic, onion and soup mix.
Rub into the holes thoroughly.
Wrap in foil.
Before sealing foil, pour mushroom soup over roast.
Seal tightly and cook at 300° for 5 or 6 hours in oven.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Soften bread in milk; add egg, meat, salt and pepper.
Shape into meatballs.
Slice potatoes into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add chopped onion.
Mix soup with water. Add meatballs to potatoes and onion.
Pour soup over entire casserole.
Cover and bake in a 400° oven until meatballs are done and potatoes are tender.

title: easy baked beans
directions: In
a
12-inch Dutch oven fry bacon until crisp.
Drain most of	the grease.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients. Bake for 2 1/2 hours with 10 coals on the top and 10 on the bottom.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with the chopped nuts and coconut.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix confectioners sugar, oleo and sour cream; glob on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baker baracho beans
directions: Cook for 2 1/2 hours at a slow boil. Add cilantro at end and serve over rice.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, then eggs and beat well.
Add bananas with milk; stir.
Add dry ingredients and raisins.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 45 minutes).
Makes 2 loaves or 24 small muffins.

title: very simple popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat.
Spread over popcorn.
Form balls with hands lubricated with margarine.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat in roaster pan with a small amount of grease drippings or salad oil.
Add flour as for gravy.
Add chopped vegetables.
Add enough water to cover entire mixture.
Cover; let simmer for 2 hours.
Delicious served on dry toast.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth; cook and stir constantly until mixture bubbles. Cook for 1 minute, remove from heat and set aside.

title: yummy bars
directions: Mix together 1 stick of butter (melted), 1 egg and cake mix. Mold in bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan.
In separate bowl combine cream cheese (softened), 1 stick melted butter, vanilla, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Mix together and pour over chocolate layer. Pour chocolate chips over cream cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put ground beef in crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Cook 2 hours on high.
Serve with Fritos or Tostitos chips.

title: creamy nutcracker fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil for 6 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour over chocolate and marshmallow.
Beat until melted.
Add nuts. Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let stand several hours before cutting.
Store in cool place.

title: jambalaya
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 4-quart pot, fry bacon until brown, but not crisp.
Remove bacon from drippings, drain and reserve.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy. Blend or sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add chopped walnuts and grated lemon rind. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Let stand for 20 minutes. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Heat egg nog.
Dissolve gelatin in water and add to egg nog. Remove from heat and add beaten eggs.
Cool.
Beat whipping cream until fluffy; add vanilla and fold into egg nog mixture.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve the next day.
Store in refrigerator.

title: spinach apple salad
directions: Remove stems from the spinach; wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Combine the spinach, apple and celery in large bowl.
Combine the vinegar and remaining ingredients in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over the spinach mixture and toss well.
Serves 4.
One serving = 61 calories, 1 g. protein, 8 g carbohydrates, 4 g fat, 51 mg. sodium. One serving = 2 vegetables + 1 fat + 1/2 fruit.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses soften; then stir together until well mixed.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce; stir until combined.
Shape into a ball and cover with pecans or serve in a bowl as a dip or spread.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and form into rolls.
Let set in cold place overnight. Slice into thin slices and bake.
Then eat!

title: pie crust - shell(low-fat)
directions: Combine flour and salt in a medium bowl.
Mix oil and milk together with a fork.
Add flour; mix with hands until just mixed. Add a little cold water if more liquid is needed.
Chill for about 10 minutes.
Roll out until large enough to fit a 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or can be baked with filling.

title: party snacks
directions: Brown meats; drain well.
Add cut up cheese slices and seasonings and stir until cheese is melted.
Spread mixture on party sliced bread and place on cookie sheets in single layers, then freeze.
To serve, bake frozen for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger beans
directions: Brown meat and onions, add bell peppers.
Drain and add other ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into dish and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish style bell peppers
directions: Saute in oil, chopped onion and chopped garlic until brown. Add ground meat and fry until done.
Add 1/2 cup flour and allow to brown.
Add chili powder and mix with meat.
Then add tomato paste.
Add enough water to make mixture sticky.
Stir well.
Salt to taste and let simmer for a few minutes until thick.
Prepare cornbread mix according to directions.
Bake.
Add 1/2 of cornbread to meat mixture.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Top with cheese and cook in a 350° oven until peppers are done.

title: yum yum dessert
directions: Combine crackers, sugar and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat milk and pudding together; stir in ice cream.
Pour over crumbs and refrigerate.
Spread whipped topping over top. Sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired (pistachios, pecans or walnuts).

title: seven layer pea salad
directions: Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: more
directions: Cook spaghetti. Drain and set aside. Brown beef and sausage together. Drain if needed. Add other ingredients and mix well. Add spaghetti. Pour into 9 x 13 dish. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: mexicali chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place oats and seasonings in blender or food processor and blend.
Coat chicken with oat mixture.
Place on rack in pan.
Brush chicken with margarine.
Bake 40 minutes or until juices run clear when pierced with a fork.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring tea to a boil.
Add remainder of ingredients and mix well.

title: betty's eggs ole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 12-inch baking dish with butter.
Line bottom of dish with chiles.
Slice cheese into medium size pieces and place on chiles.
In bowl, beat eggs and sour cream until well blended.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chiles and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray pizza pan with Pam. Cover the bottom with zucchini. Prepare Pizza Sauce and pour over zucchini slices. Sprinkle the top with meat, mushrooms, green pepper and cheese. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: bird feeders
directions: Combine corn meal, peanut butter and bird seed.
Tie a string on pine cones.
Smear cones with mixture and hang up outside for the birds.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Drain beans that have soaked overnight.
Add fresh, cold water to cover beans well.
Add to this the onions, green pepper, garlic, parsley, ham bone, black, red and cayenne peppers, bay leaves and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook slow, but keep bubbling, until beans are tender, about 3 hours.
Salt to taste after ham cubes have blended with mixture.
Continue cooking until a thick gravy has formed.
Add water from time to time during cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: easy as 1, 2, 3 salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate. Do not cover or it will get watery.

title: ham and cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13 baking dish. Line bottom of pan with half the bread cubes, sprinkle with ham and cheeses. Top with remaining bread.

title: seafoam
directions: Dissolve jello in hot pear juice.
Add cream cheese (softened) and blend until smooth.
Chill mixture until slightly thickened. Add Cool Whip and beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour in mold and chill until firm.

title: pear bread
directions: Stir and mix well the first three ingredients. Add the oil, eggs, sugar, pears and vanilla. "Pam" the pans and fill 3/4 full. Cook 1 hour at 325°.

title: spicy pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In Dutch oven over medium heat, cook and stir chicken in oil until chicken is lightly brown.
Stir in pasta sauce, cream and basil; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Stir in cooked pasta and Parmesan cheese; turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover.
Bake 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Top with parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: brisket carbonnade
directions: Pour all ingredients on beef brisket.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours, covered with foil, or in a slow cooker for 10 hours.

title: chunk ham fettuccine
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to pkg, while cooking peas according to pkg; set aside. Prepare white sauce according to pkg using 1/4 c. milk; stir in nutmeg. In pan fettuccine was cooking in, combine hot drained fettuccine, white sauce, peas, ham and cheese.

title: apricot chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken on bottom of pan.
Mix ingredients together. Pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes (no cover) at 350°.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Cook broccoli; let cool.
Chop broccoli and crabmeat in small pieces; put in bowl.
Add mayonnaise.
Serve cold.
Delicious.

title: applesauce cake bars
directions: Sift first 8 ingredients together. Add applesauce, eggs and shortening.
Using mixer at low speed, beat just until moistened. Increase speed to medium.
Beat 3 minutes.
Spread in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes clean. Cool.
Makes 48 bars.

title: string bean delight
directions: Brown hamburg with diced onions.
Add string beans, whole tomatoes and sliced onions.
Mix and then push into rings.
Place in baking pan and place in oven at 350° about 1 1/2 hours, until moisture is absorbed.
Add cheese and top with mashed potatoes. Make sure to cover top of pan.
Place in oven again for 20 minutes.

title: israeli honey cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
With electric mixer at medium speed, mix shortening, egg, vanilla and honey until very light and fluffy.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture, oats, nuts, raisins and chocolate.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Follow directions on the box.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of butter and mix in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly over medium heat until mixture thickens. Add onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread cubes.
Cool.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: crab sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients; slice bread in approximately 1-inch thick slices.
Spread mixture over bread slices.
Place on baking sheet; broil at 350° until cheese melts.
Garnish with paprika, optional. Serves 8 to 10.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned.
Drain fat.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust. Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, margarine, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: my way sandwich
directions: Spread cream cheese on 1 slice of bread.
Add chopped veggies to top of cream cheese.
Add onion slice.
Add salami.
Top with another slice of bread.
Nice change of pace.

title: mom ford's biscuits
directions: Stir all and let rise.
Turn out on floured board.
Cut into biscuits.
Let rise again.
Put butter on top and bake at 400° until brown.

title: ginger raisin cookies
directions: Use a large bowl.
Mix all ingredients except raisins.
Add raisins and mix well.
Use a small spoon and drop on a greased pan.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: golden potato
directions: Cover potatoes with boiling salted water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes until fork-tender.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onions in butter until soft, but not brown.
Sprinkle with flour. Add salt and pepper. Slowly add half and half, cooking and stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add mustard and mayonnaise.
Stir until well blended.
Sauce will be thick and creamy.
Turn potatoes into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and thyme.
Serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into well-greased cake pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine rice and corn; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Add onion and beef.
Pour second can of tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water over this.
Lay 4 strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° covered for 1 hour and 1/2 hour without cover.

title: pickled beets
directions: Remove beet tops, leaving roots and 1-inch steam.
Cover with boiling water and cook until tender.
Drain and reserve 1 cup of cooking liquid.
Remove skins.
Combine cooking liquid, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Add spices tied in thin white cloth.
Heat to boiling.
Add beets and onions.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove spice bag; continue simmering while quickly packing beets and onions into one hot pint jar at a time.
Fill to within 1/2-inch of jar top.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath (212°) for 30 minutes.
Remove jars from canner and complete seals unless closures are self-sealing type.
Makes 4 pints.

title: no fat pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients well for 4 minutes.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old southern corn pone
directions: Dissolve soda and baking powder in milk.
Place cornmeal in bowl.
Add salt and shortening.
Mix well with fingertips.
Add milk until you have a very stiff batter.
Shape into pones (round flattened cakes) and place on well-greased pan.
Bake in a very hot oven.

title: ham raisin sauce
directions: Boil raisins and water 5 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients and add to raisins and water.
Continue cooking on medium heat until thickened.
Add vinegar.
Stir well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve hot on ham.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until filling sets.
May be frozen for later use.
Other spices may be used if desired.

title: pecan praline
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in a large bowl. Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in a 2-cup microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir. Microwave at High 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes and mix well.
Pour over the cereal mixture evenly; bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes. Spread and cool on cookie sheet.
Makes 10 cups.

title: bud's anchor inn fish batter
directions: Combine.
Fold into the mixture 1 stiffly beaten egg white. Make ahead and let set at least 1 hour before using.
Dip fish in batter and fry until golden brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute onion and green pepper in butter until soft.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until rice has absorbed all liquid.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mint meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix salt and cream of tartar and add to sugar then add this gradually to egg whites.
Add vanilla and lemon juice then fold in the chocolate bits.
Add 4 to 5 drops of green food coloring.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Put in oven.
Turn off heat. Leave in oven 8 hours.
Take out and serve.

title: cowboy coffeecake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and margarine until crumbly; reserve 1/2 cup.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, soda and spices. Mix well.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well.

title: shrimp mediterranean
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture over shrimp and let sit for 1 hour in the refrigerator. Place the shrimp on skewers.
Grill over hot coals for 2 minutes on side one. Baste with reserved marinade. Turn and baste the other side. Cook for 3 minutes.

title: al's fried venison steak
directions: Rub the steak with a mixture of salt and pepper.
Dip in flour or cracker crumbs; saute in hot fat until browned on both sides. Place on a hot dish; cover to keep warm.
Dredge 2 teaspoons of flour into fat in bottom of pan; stir until brown.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon of currant jelly in 1 cup boiling water.
Add to gravy and stir.
Strain, pour over the meat and serve.

title: melba delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients together and mix well.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and dessert topping. Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
When pudding sets, spread on top of cheese layer.
Garnish with topping and more nuts.

title: leah rose's quick dessert
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherries.
Sprinkle oatmeal and nut meats over cake mixture.
Melt butter and drizzle over to dampen.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sherried chicken fingers
directions: Slice chicken breasts into quarters (eighths if large).
Wash in milk, then dredge in bread crumbs.
Brown lightly in heated olive oil.
Remove to a 12 x 7-inch Pyrex pan.
Add sherry to hot frying pan with chicken drippings.
Reduce about 1 minute, then pour over chicken.
Place chicken in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve with Blue cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: ambrosia oriental salad
directions: Place lettuce in bowl and other ingredients. Drain fruit real good.

title: delicious brisket
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over brisket.
Roast in covered roaster, fat side up, at 325° for 40 minutes per pound.
The last 20 minutes should be cooked, uncovered.
Baste frequently during last 20 minutes.
Cool it.
Slice it.
Reheat at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onions
in
cooking
oil.
Mix tomatoes, water, parsley, salt, sugar,
garlic,
pepper and oregano in a bowl. Pour in with beef and
onions.
Cook 30 minutes on low, uncovered.

title: onion-mushroom gravy
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix soup mix and flour. Stir in water. Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes, or until gravy is thickened. Makes about 2 cups of gravy.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar in a bowl.
Add egg and molasses; beat thoroughly.
Combine flour, baking soda, spices and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix until blended.
Shape dough into teaspoonfuls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Arrange balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes. Cool cookies on racks.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and add condensed milk.
Stir in nuts and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in a pan and freeze.
Cut into squares when ready to serve.

title: 24-hour cuke salad
directions: Combine water and vinegar.
Add sugar and stir until it is dissolved.
Add salad oil, salt and pepper.
Peel cucumber and score lengthwise with a fork.
Slice thinly.
Peel onion; slice thinly and separate into rings.
Put into vinegar mixture and mix lightly.
Cover; refrigerate at least one hour and up to 24 hours.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt; bring to full boil over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Add milk chocolate morsels and semi-sweet morsels; stir until morsels melt and mixture is well blended.
Stir in nuts and vanilla extract.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill in refrigerator until firm (about 2 hours).
Cut into squares.

title: honey of a chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and basil.
Mix next 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Turn chicken in this mixture and lay skin side up in a shallow, greased baking pan.
Keep basting with sauces.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients; press in crock-pot and cook on low heat for 4 hours.
Use a pair of forks to remove from crock-pot.

title: pete's delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix together nuts, margarine and flour and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix well and chill.
If too thick, add more milk.
It is delicious and only takes 2 or 3 minutes to make.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: In large skillet heat oil and cook chicken, onion and pepper until chicken is cooked.
Add corn, chicken broth and salsa and bring to boil.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Wash, pare and slice apples into a bowl and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and lemon rind together.
Add apples; toss.
Arrange in a 9-inch deep dish pie pan and dot with butter.
Roll out pastry; mark top and adjust on top of apples.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Stir salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Place chicken in a glass dish.
Spread sauce over chicken.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cover with aluminum foil, while baking.

title: ham and lima beans
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir together well.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 10 hours.
If on high, cook only 4 to 5 hours. Serve with wedges of hot corn bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in a large pot; debone and cut up in small pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with boiled eggs.
Mix soup and broth together and pour over eggs.
Mix the oleo, flour, milk and pepper together and pour mixture over all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut up chicken and put in bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Mix 2-1/4 cups chicken broth and 1 can of cream of chicken or celery soup and cook until boiling.
Pour over chicken.
Put sliced eggs over the top.
Mix in a separate bowl 1/2 stick of butter, 1 cup flour, 1/4 tsp pepper, cup milk, and 1/4 cup of mayonnaise.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 400 degrees from 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.

title: tuna dip(servings:  6)
directions: Put above ingredients into electric blender; blend well.
If necessary, thin with milk.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Also makes a good sandwich.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in 4 pieces.
Cook in water 20 minutes.
Add salt. Cool and tear in pieces and put a layer of cabbage.
Add bread crumbs, cheese sauce and mushroom soup.
Add another layer and top with cheese sauce and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon filling
directions: In saucepan, mix the sugar, cornstarch and dash of salt.
Add water, egg yolk and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add lemon peel and butter.
Cool.
Makes 4 cups.

title: crabmeat cheese ball
directions: Pour over top of meatball and serve with crackers.

title: apricot jewels
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in margarine and cream cheese using pastry blender or fork, until mixture is crumbly.
Add coconut and preserves.
Blend well. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown; cool before frosting.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In 1 1/2 to 2-quart Pyrex dish, spread pie filling.
Spread cake mix over pie filling.
Cover cake mix with nuts.
Melt butter and pour evenly over nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven until top is brown and juice is coming to the top, about 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk, salt and butter until it forms a soft ball. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat with a spoon until stiff.
Pour onto buttered plate.
Cool, then cut into pieces.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in 4 cups salted water.
Add other ingredients until butter melts.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 325°.
Add jalapenos if desired.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; dust with powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Combine egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup water and salt in top of double boiler; blend.
Add gelatin.
Place over boiling water; beat constantly until thick and fluffy, approximately 5 minutes.
Cool.
Place peanut butter in bowl.
Add remaining 1/2 cup water gradually; beat until smooth.
Add vanilla to egg yolk mixture; blend.
Chill until slightly thickened, but still syrupy.
Beat egg white until foamy. Add remaining sugar gradually, beating until stiff.
Fold into peanut butter mixture.
Turn into crumb crust.
Chill until firm. Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: sparkle paint
directions: Mix flour, salt and water.
Add tempera until the desired color is obtained.
Finished product will dry "sparkly."
(Less water will create more sparkle.)

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape dough in rolls; place rolls in wax paper and refrigerate.
These can be frozen and baked any time.
Slice with a knife.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: cross-patch potatoes
directions: Wash and wipe potatoes.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Score tops in 1/2-inch squares, making cuts 1/2-inch deep.
Brush skins and tops with shortening.
Bake in 450° oven 40 to 50 minutes or until brown and tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken with chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with 1 roll of Ritz crackers (crushed) and 1 stick of butter (melted).
Optional:
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: strever oyster dressing
directions: Break up crackers.
Cut up oysters.
Use oyster juice, too. Combine together.
Grease casserole dish with Pam cooking spray. Add milk to cracker/oyster mixture.
Add small amounts of milk if more is needed.
Not mushy, not soggy, just damp.
Combine gently. Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: individual italian eggplant
directions: For sauce, heat oil in large saucepan or Dutch oven over medium-low heat.
Add chopped onion and garlic and cook, stirring frequently, 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and their juice, breaking up tomatoes with large spoon.
Add tomato sauce, chopped green pepper, rosemary, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 1 hour.
Add onion and green pepper pieces and continue simmering 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
While sauce simmers, peel eggplant, remove ends, and slice lengthwise into 1/2 inch thick slices.
Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly grease baking pan large enough to hold eggplant in a single layer.
In shallow bowl, whisk together milk and eggs until well blended.
In separate shallow bowl, mix bread crumbs, parsley flakes, parmesan cheese, and dressing mix. Coat eggplant with flour, shaking off excess.
Dip into milk mixture, then into bread mixture, coating evenly.
Place in baking pan. Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until very tender.
Spoon enough sauce onto eggplant to cover.
Top with cheese slices.
Continue baking 1 minute or until cheese melts.
Spoon remaining sauce onto serving plate and top with eggplant.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mrs. bodie's potato salad
directions: Add eggs and onion to potatoes.
Mix mayonnaise with remaining ingredients and add to potatoes.
Adjust mayonnaise amount to suit individual preference for creaminess.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Cook on low heat 5 minutes.
Place biscuits in greased muffin tins, pressing to cover bottoms and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup meat mixture into biscuit cups and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and food coloring.
Add pineapple, strawberries and nuts.
Mix well.
Add lemon concentrate last; mix.
This makes the mixture stiff.
Put into 2 pie shells and refrigerate.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, juice and rind.
Stir in gradually the buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes approximately 5 1/2 cups.

title: delicious pumpkin pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, spices and flour.
Stir in egg yolks, milk, cream and pumpkin.
Cook, stirring over medium heat, until thickened.
Spoon into pie shells.

title: macaroons
directions: Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 48 cookies.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil the hen in a large quantity of water with the onion, green pepper and celery until chicken is ready to pull off the bone.
Remove hen from the stock.
Bone and cut into bite sizes. Set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and cheese.
Crumble sausage into mixture.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green chili squash casserole
directions: Steam in covered skillet the squash, onion, oleo and seasonings. Add chicken soup and eggs. Spread jalapeno Cheez Whiz in 2-quart rectangular glass casserole.
Put squash mixture on cheese and spread chilies over evenly and top with stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix together coconut and chopped nuts; press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix as directed and pour over coconut and nut mixture.
In a separate bowl, mix together remaining ingredients and drop on top of cake using a teaspoon. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cake should look like an earthquake goes right through the middle when done.

title: chunky orange-lemon salsa
directions: In a small nonstick saucepan, heat the vinegar over medium heat.
Add the scallions; cook for 1 minute.
Mix in the honey; cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the tomatoes, oranges (or tangerines), lemon juice and pimientos.
Heat briefly. Refrigerate for up to 1 week.
Yields 2 cups.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice, then mix with cream of chicken soup, butter and rice together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then put cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Cook sugar and water to soft ball stage (236°).
Gradually add to beaten egg whites, beating until mixture forms peaks.
Will frost top and sides of 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Layer ingredients in order in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After about 25 minutes, cut through the cake with a knife in several places to let the juice come to the top.
Serve hot or cold.

title: marbled peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Divide mixture into 2 portions.
Stir peanut butter into 1 portion.
Stir chocolate chips into other portion until melted.
Pour peanut butter mixture into pan.
Top with chocolate mixture.
Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.

title: chicken 'n' dressing
directions: Toss stuffing.
Mix with half can of the soup, chicken broth and beaten eggs.
Spread mixture in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Top with cooked chicken.
Combine remaining half can of soup with milk and pimentos.
Pour over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bogberry apple tart
directions: Grease a 9 inch pie pan or 8 inch square pan.
Layer apples in pan.
Alternate cranberries with apples.
Combine chopped nuts, cinnamon, salt and 1/4 c. sugar and sprinkle over fruit.
In a bowl, mix brown sugar, white sugar, eggs, vanilla, butter and flour.
Pour mixture over apples and berries, spreading evenly to cover (mixture will run down through the fruit).
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until knife inserted into the center comes out clean.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: dee's garlic mashed potatoes casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; mash (or use recipe for instant potatoes for 10 servings).
Add sour cream, cream cheese and Parmesan cheese; whip with mixer.
Add salt and pepper to taste and 3/4 teaspoon garlic powder or more.
Put into baking dish.
Crumble pieces of crisp bacon.
Chop green onions.
Mix with bacon and sprinkle over top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Better to add butter the last 1/2 hour to prevent burning.

title: holly's finger-lickin-good biscuits
directions: First add flour, then mix shortening into flour and enough milk to make workable dough.
Mix well.
Then roll it out about 1/2 to 3/4 inch tall, then cut out the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baking powder coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, egg yolks and butter.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased pan.
Spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hard-boiled egg cookies
directions: Mash egg yolks.
Mix dry ingredients together and add mashed egg yolks and butter.
Mix well. This will be like pie dough. Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Brush with beaten egg whites.
Can also top with nuts if desired.
Bake at 350°.

title: mary's cream wafers
directions: Mix butter, cream and flour thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Transfer to wax paper, heavily sprinkle with sugar (granulated), both sides.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick 4 times with fork.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until slightly puffy. Put two together with filling.

title: linda's blueberry muffins
directions: Sift the

dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl. Combine egg, oil and milk; add to the dry ingredients. Stir just until all is blended. Fold in the blueberries. Fill paper lined muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake in hot 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter.
Add the cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, salt, flour and apples.
Stir until mixed well. Bake for 1 hour (approximately) at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: In
a
large
bowl,
combine spinach, celery, onion and eggs. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium
saucepan,
melt
butter; stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring
to
a boil; boil and stir 2 minutes.	Remove from heat;
stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in confectioners sugar;
beat
until
smooth.
Spread
into	buttered 9-inch square baking pan; chill until firm.
Cut into squares; makes 3 1/3 pounds.

title: summer's harvest salad
directions: Prepare macaroni.
Add broccoli during last two minutes of cooking time; drain.
Combine macaroni, broccoli, shrimp, tomato, spinach and red onion.
Blend together Italian dressing, Salad Supreme seasoning and salt.
Toss dressing with salad mixture. Garnish with egg and sprinkle with Salad Supreme.
Serve immediately or cover and chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together all ingredients except pastry. Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Place pastry over casserole.
Crimp edges to seal; cut slits.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in 9 x 13 pan.
Pour pineapple over pie filling and mix with spoon.
Sprinkle 2 boxes Jiffy cake mix over filling.
Cut butter into pats and place on top of cake mix. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: ice cream in a bag
directions: Mix in a bowl, then put in sandwich Ziploc bag.
Put into a large Ziploc bag (quart size) with crushed ice and salt.
Shake. Makes one serving.

title: low cholesterol sugar cookies(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla together until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder, mixing well.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Roll small portions of dough at a time on a lightly floured board.
Cut out shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Serving of 2 cookies equals 1 fat exchange.

title: quick chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 3 minutes at rapid boil.
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Allow to cool and harden.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise together; set aside.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix until blended. Beat at medium speed four minutes. Turn into greased and floured 10 inch cake pan. Bake 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: shrimp quiches
directions: Generously grease 2 dozen 1 3/4-inch muffin cups; set aside. Separate rolls into 12 equal pieces.
Cut each in half; press each half into bottom and side of a muffin cup.
Divide shrimp evenly among pastry shells.
Beat together egg, cream, onion, salt and cayenne until well blended.
Using about 2 teaspoons for each, divide evenly among shells.
Sprinkle cheese over tops.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 20 minutes, or until edges are brown and center appears set.
Cool 5 minutes to serve warm, or remove from pans and cool completely on racks, then package airtight and freeze.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat. Add apples. Sift flour, soda, and salt together. Add to creamed mixture. Add orange rind, vanilla, and nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350 in loaf pan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Layer beef, Veg-All and soup until all gone.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: no-bake peanut butter treats
directions: Place several pieces wax paper on counter.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture comes to the boil.
Remove from heat and cool for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter; stir to blend.
Add oats, nuts and vanilla; stir to mix well.
Quickly drop mixture by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Cool completely.
Peel away from paper and turn candies over to dry for 1 hour.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix cocoa with boiling water.
Add butter, stir until dissolved; cool mixture.
Sift flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Mix these ingredients slowly into cocoa mixture then add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 9-inch Bundt pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Whip 1 pint whipping cream in bowl.
Add a little powdered sugar to taste and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Makes a very light frosting.

title: party chicken
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam butter spray. Cut each boneless breast in half. Wrap each half with one slice of bacon. Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and sliced mushrooms. Pour soup mixture over chicken. Bake in 275° oven for 4 hours.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Combine peel, juice and egg.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just enough to moisten.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool, wrap and store overnight before slicing.

title: granny's no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix oleo and vanilla wafer crumbs together with hands.
Add other ingredients, dry things first, like coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Add cherry juice.
Pack into glass dish and cover.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: steak casserole
directions: Sear ground meat.
Slice onions and potatoes thin.
Arrange everything in layers in casserole:
1/2 meat, onions, sprouts, potatoes, 1/2 tomato soup, etc.
End with thin layer of potatoes on top and rest of soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: almond roca
directions: Melt butter and sugar in heavy iron skillet until mocha color. Pour
in
almonds,
they will crack.
Spread on cookie sheet with sides.
Put
chocolate
bar
on top.
It will melt, then spread evenly
over
candy.
Put nuts on top of chocolate while still soft.
Cool; break in pieces.

title: shrimp-wild rice salad
directions: The night before, cook rice.
Add curry and Italian dressing. Chill overnight.
Toss marinated rice with other ingredients just before serving.
Line bowl with lettuce leaves.
Add salad and garnish with cherry tomatoes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sausage vegetable stew
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large saucepan, mix cornstarch, onion, bouillon, basil and salt.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, undrained carrots and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add sausage and potatoes.
Heat until bubbly. Turn into 2-quart casserole; arrange biscuits over top.
Sprinkle seeds on top.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable minestrone
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook the onion, the celery and the garlic in the olive oil until tender but not brown.
Stir in the water, undrained tomatoes, cubed potato, bay leaf, basil, salt, sage and pepper.
Bring to boiling; stir in noodles.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, about 10 minutes or until noodles are al dente.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: breakfast cake (cinnamon flops)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pan and put lumps of butter the size of peas over cake.
Sprinkle 1 cup brown sugar and cinnamon over cake.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese; pour one-half the batter into a hot greased skillet and sprinkle with cheese.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake 20 minutes until brown.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Brown meat in a large saucepot.
Spoon off fat.
Mix mushroom soup, onion soup and 1 cup water.
Pour over meat.
Reduce heat. Cover and cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables. Cover and cook about 45 minutes or until vegetables and meat are tender.
Remove meat and vegetables. Stir together 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup water. Stir into soup mixture and cook until boils and thickens.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box. Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured pan. Beat rest of ingredients (except egg whites and milk). Set aside. Beat egg whites until foamy. Pour into rest of the batter with just enough milk to pour easily over batter. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Cake is done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in blender.
Whirl for 2 seconds at high speed.
Gradually add oil.

title: whoopie pies(an old amish recipe with oatmeal)
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening or butter.
Add eggs, then add salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add soda, dissolved in hot water.
Gradually add flour and oats.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until brown.
Cool.
Spread a dab of filling on the flat side of the cookie, then top with another cookie to form a pie.
Refrigerate until eaten.
Enjoy.
Makes about 3 dozen pies.

title: coffee cake
directions: Crem together sugar and butter.
Add sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking powder.

title: yellow rice
directions: Place in a pot the rice and water and mix.
Add the garlic and salt mix, onion and garlic and mix.
Add the Goya cilantro and archiote and mix.
The last item is the olive oil.
