Mix well and cook until the water is boiling.
Reduce the flame to a simmer and cook until the water is absorbed and the rice looks cooked to your taste.

title: old-fashioned apple butter
directions: Fill slow cooker 3/4 full with applesauce.
Add sugar and stir well.
Cook, covered, overnight on low heat; then cook, uncovered, on high the next day until it is thickened.
Stir in vinegar and cinnamon oil.
Stir frequently while cooking.
Pour hot apple butter in hot sterilized jars; seal with paraffin.

title: chocolate frosty(like wendy's)
directions: Mix and pour into electric ice cream freezer. Freeze just as you would homemade ice cream.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer cauliflower, lettuce, onion and bacon.
Mix mayo, sugar, Parmesan, salt and pepper.
Spread on top of salad.
Top with cheese and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well, using a fork.
Drop by tablespoons into hot, lightly oiled electric frying pan.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Serve with biscuits and gravy.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Cook until crisp; drain.
Combine eggs, cream and seasonings.
Beat until well blended.
Sprinkle bacon over bottom of pastry shell, then cheese.
Pour egg/cream mixture over cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 main dish or 12 appetizer size servings.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and chill.
Tastes like shrimp.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Melt butter or margarine and stir in flour, making a roux. Add milk and stir until thick and smooth.
Add seasonings, garlic and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts and mixture bubbles. Add mushrooms. Slice or cube chicken into bite-sized pieces and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with artichokes and sauce. Mix crumbs or Rice Krispies and butter. Sprinkle over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: homemade hominy
directions: Put lye in iron kettle.
Add one pint of cold water.
When lye is dissolved, add one gallon boiling water and stir thoroughly. Add shelled corn.
Bring to boiling point; boil 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
If mixture cooks down, add more boiling water.
When the husk is off corn, it is ready to wash.
Wash corn. Fill the kettle with cold water.
Wash 4 or 5 times.
Cover with cold water; bring to boil and cook 4 hours.
When done, you should have 7 quarts of hominy.

title: tutti frutti
directions: Put marshmallows into a large bowl; pour the juice of fruit cocktail over it.
Let this stand in the refrigerator overnight. In the morning, stir this; add the fruit cocktail, Cool Whip and pineapple.
Whip the heavy cream and mix thoroughly.
Put into a glass bowl and serve.

title: plum kuchen
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in other ingredients.
Spread batter evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Mix together.
Spread in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine liquid, vinegar, sugar, salt and cloves.
Heat to boiling.
Add beets and heat again.
Serve the following day.

title: pavlova
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add half the sugar.
Beat well, then add the rest and beat well again.
Fold in the vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in cornflour and baking powder, then add the water.
Keep folding.
Place mixture on flat, greased tray.
It is best to have a sheet of greaseproof paper between the mixture and the tray.
Set oven to 350°, then turn down to 300° when you have put the pavlova into the oven.
Cook for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake filled dessert
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients; save 1/2 cup crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8 x 8-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Let cool.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large, nonstick skillet, brown meat and onion.
Spread cottage cheese over meat, then uncooked noodles.
In a small bowl, mix tomatoes and seasonings together.
Pour over noodles.
Cover; cook over medium heat for 20 minutes, or until noodles are almost tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand for 5 minutes.

title: garlic bread sticks
directions: Combine softened margarine and garlic powder and paprika. Trim crusts from 8 slices white bread, if desired.
Spread both sides of bread with margarine.
Cut each slice into four sticks. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry cream cheese mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water and cinnamon. Pour 2 cups of the gelatin into medium bowl.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable oil spray.
In large mixing bowl, cream margarine until soft.
Add the sugars and beat until creamy.
Mix in egg whites, peanut butter and soda.
Add flour; mix constantly.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Roll dough into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with the back of a floured fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Mix the warm water, yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar; set aside to dissolve.
Combine all ingredients.
Add flour as needed.
Mix and knead twice.
Roll out, cut and turn in 1/4 stick of butter in pan.

title: dieter's corn bread
directions: Mix well and bake at 450° until brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Combine margarine, flour and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: baked custard
directions: Heat milk, sugar and salt; add lightly beaten eggs slowly to the hot milk mixture.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into custard dishes.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake in a pan of hot water until custard is set (when the point of a knife comes out clean, then the custard is done).
Remove the custard dishes from the hot water and serve.
This is to be baked at 375°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Dredge meat (both sides) with flour, salt and pepper.
Melt about 4 tablespoons shortening in Dutch oven.
Brown meat on both sides.
Remove meat from pan.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons flour; mix well.
Add more shortening if need be to make a thin paste.
Add 3 to 4 cups cool water and coffee.
Stir until begins to thicken; add onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Should have a fairly thin gravy.
Add meat; cover and place in a 350° oven.
Bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours until done.

title: easy chicken
directions: Lightly grease a roasting pan and spread uncooked rice in prepared pan.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.
Combine juice, soup and dry soup mix and pour over chicken.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Dip bread into mixture, one at a time.
Pan-fry in butter or oleo on both sides until golden brown.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top of slices.

title: nacho platter ole
directions: Microwave beans and salsa in 1 1/2-quart bowl for 2 to 3 minutes.
Spoon into center of large serving platter.
Arrange chips around bean mixture.
Microwave process cheese spread according to label directions; pour over chips.
If desired, garnish with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, green onion slices and pitted ripe olive slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: many way meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt; shape into 16 meatballs.
In skillet, brown meatballs; pour off fat.
Stir in soup, water and parsley.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend together potato chips, pepper and curry powder.
Mix together eggs, orange juice and water.
Lightly salt chicken.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in seasoned potato chips.
Place chicken pieces, side by side in a greased pan.
Drizzle with melted butter and bake until tender, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Brown turkey.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes and then serve on rolls.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and nuts in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine. Spread over top of batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chess cheese squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chuck wagon peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, sugar and salt together, then cut in shortening and peanut butter.
Blend in 1/2 cup corn syrup. Place dough on waxed paper and shape into rolls.
Chill; cut in slices about 1/8-inch thick.
Place 1/2 of slices on baking sheet. Place 1 teaspoon peanut butter on each slice.
Cover with remaining slices.
Seal edges with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain well.

Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion, then blend into cooked broccoli. Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese. Melt margarine; add stuffing crumbs, tossing to mix well. Sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until real bubbly.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together eggs, salt and oil. Add muffin mix, corn and sour cream. Mix well by hand. Pour into well greased 8-inch square pan (or large iron skillet). Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm.

title: holiday rice
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add next 4 ingredients and saute until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken broth and seasonings; stir well.
Spoon rice mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is done.

title: easy pistachio ambrosia
directions: Mix together the canned fruit.
Add unprepared pudding mix. Blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray or butter baking dish and sprinkle dry onion soup in bottom of dish.
Mix rice, soup and broth together; pour in dish. Place chicken on top of rice and cover.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°. Uncover dish.
Brown chicken 10 minutes.

title: easy barbecue
directions: Cook roast in crock-pot covered with water for 6 to 8 hours. String meat.
Put in skillet.
Add sugar, onion and barbecue sauce.
Cook until thick, about 45 minutes.

title: christmas holly cookies
directions: Melt slowly in saucepan the marshmallows and butter.
Stir in food coloring and vanilla.
Place corn flakes in large bowl; stir in above mixture.
Place by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheets. Press 2 candies on each and chill in refrigerator.

title: string bean salad
directions: Open the beans in half, so seasoning will go through.
Salt to taste (garlic salt).
Combine in bowl, cover, let stand in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours, drain and serve.

title: tea punch(servings: 24 to 30)
directions: Mix all together.
Do not dilute concentrated juice.
Serve with plenty of ice.
Delicious on a hot summer day!

title: fantastic corn on the cob
directions: Boil corn for 15 minutes.
Remove from water and place in rectangular dish.
Sprinkle with spices and add butter.
Sprinkle corn with Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish with foil and place in warm oven until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook vegetables in chicken broth 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients except cheese, mixing well. Place in large baking dish. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil sugar, butter and syrup for 1 minute.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture over 1/2 of the corn.
Stir until coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Be sure to stir every 15 minutes.
Repeat with remaining popcorn and mixture.

title: fruit sauce for ham
directions: Mix above ingredients in a saucepan; heat, stirring constantly, for about 2 minutes.
Just before ham is baked, pour over ham and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: cheese dip
directions: Recommend at least one ingredient be hot to give dip a spicy taste.

title: tomato grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In a saucepan, bring water and milk to a boil.
Add salt and slowly add grits.
Return to a boil, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Reduce heat, cover and cook for 3 minutes.
While stirring the grits, add 1/2 c. butter and stir until butter is melted.
Cover and cook for 3 - 5 minutes or until grits are thick and creamy.
Remove from heat and set aside. Using a skillet, saute onions in remaining Tbsp. butter for 1 minute. Add processed cheese, garlic powder, 1 1/2 c. c. cheddar cheese and onions to grits.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add tomatoes and chilies.
Mix well, pour grits into greased 8 x 11 x 2 casserole pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over casserole for last 5 minutes of cooking time.

title: easy slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and stir with a whisk until well blended.
Mix with chopped cabbage.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add flour, parsley, garlic and crawfish.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add half and half and diced cheese.
Cook over low heat (20 to 30 minutes).
Boil noodles; drain.
Mix noodles and crawfish mixture together.
Pour into large greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ham loaves
directions: Mix together and shape loaves.
Bake, covered for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove excess fat.
Mix brown sugar, salad mustard, vinegar and water.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Drizzle over ham with baster and cook uncovered for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dinner muffins
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Spread muffins with mustard.
Top each muffin with two slices ham.
Spoon on broccoli-cheese mix.

title: pork primavera
directions: In a large frypan, saute garlic and pork strips in oil until lightly browned.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Simmer for a few minutes, stirring, until moisture is almost gone.
Add wine and simmer to reduce liquid.
Pour over fettucine.
Toss all together with cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Bake potatoes; scoop out insides and put into a large mixing bowl.
Mash potatoes or put through ricer.	Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.	Add onion, eggs, flour, salt and pepper and beat until light and fluffy.
Spoon into an ungreased round 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole or souffl dish.
Sprinkle onion rings over the top.
Cover with foil.	May be refrigerated up to 2 days.
May be frozen.

title: see's fudge
directions: Bring to a hard boil the milk and sugar.
Keep stirring, not to burn.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Take off burner.
Beat in butter and chocolate chips, stirring until glossy look is gone.
Pour directly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put into refrigerator until set. Do not butter pan.

title: delicious whole wheat bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine shortening, honey, molasses, salt and milk.
Cool to lukewarm and add to yeast.
Add flour. Knead.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in bread pans.
Let rise until almost doubled, 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients. Dot with butter. Bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Boil water. Add hash browns. Add soup. Add Velveeta. Cook on low until cheese is melted. Stir often.

title: curry chicken
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix in half the oil. Put remaining half of oil in a pot and wait until very hot, then put in chicken.
Cover and reduce heat.
Let simmer until cooked. Keep stirring so that chicken does not stick to pot.
Serve with rice.

title: banana frosting
directions: Cream butter until soft and glossy.
Add half of sugar; beat until blended.
Add mashed bananas and lemon juice; blend.
Add remaining sugar; beat until frosting is light and fluffy.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Cream together sugar and mayonnaise.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cocoa and add alternately to the creamed mixture with the warm water and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beetle hats
directions: Place sliced bologna on cookie sheet.
Put mashed potatoes on top of bologna.
Cover with cheese.
Heat in oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 275°.

title: potato soup with ham
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, salt and bouillon cube in boiling water until potatoes are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a simmer.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: gumbo file
directions: Put chicken into heavy saucepot.
Add next 6 ingredients; cover and bring to boil.
Remove foam.
Simmer, covered 1 1/2 to 2 hours until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Strain broth and cool slightly.
Remove fat from surface; remove skin from chicken and meat from bones.
Dice chicken and set aside.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough (regular size) into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lillian's mushroom soup
directions: Soak mushrooms in water overnight.
Drain mushrooms from broth and rinse well, then chop in small pieces.
Strain broth through sieve with cloth at the bottom (coffee filters can be used) to remove all sand to get a clear broth.
Add 4 quarts of water to mushroom broth and add in mushrooms, onion, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Slow heat for about 1 hour.
Combine 2 teaspoons vinegar with the 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup along with 1 can of half and half and blend in 3 tablespoons of flour.
Slowly add these to soup.
Simmer another 15 minutes.
You can precook Kluski noodles and add to soup when ready to serve.

title: pasta snack
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water; drain.
Deep fry at 375° until golden.
Mix seasoned salt, onion salt and chili powder.
Coat macaroni pieces.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute garlic and onion, then add ground beef and brown.
Add soups, enchilada sauce and green chilies.
Heat thoroughly.
Crush Doritos (1/2 bag).
Layer crushed Doritos chips, meat and cheese. End up with cheese on top.
Place in 400° oven.
Heat until cheese is bubbly.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook frozen green beans in salted water.
Drain.
Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: refresco pegio(royal refreshment)
directions: Section oranges over a bowl to catch the juice.
Arrange orange sections, pineapple chunks and strawberries in a single layer on shallow baking pan; freeze.

title: crab and corn bisque
directions: Saute celery, onion and bell pepper in margarine in a Dutch oven.
Add soup, corn, half and half, milk, bay leaves, thyme, garlic powder, pepper and hot sauce.
Cook until thoroughly heated. Gently stir in crabmeat and heat thoroughly.
Remove bay leaves. Garnish with parsley and lemon slices if desired.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour in baking dish and add topping.

title: oven rice
directions: Combine rice, noodles, butter and bouillon.
Mix casserole. Add boiling water.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Fluff with a fork and serve with shrimp in herb butter.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill overnight.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans together and spread in a greased 13 x 15-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions on package and spread over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Spread over cake and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix
rhubarb, sugar and food coloring together and pour into a 9
x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over the rhubarb. Melt the margarine
and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: brownie bread with cinnamon spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat brownie and biscuit mixes, water, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into lightly greased 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain and add onion.
Saute over medium heat; add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: kyra's butter fingers
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Chill at least 1/2 hour.
Roll into 1/2-inch roll and cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces or "fingers."
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: tom's terrific garlic spread
directions: Take bread cubes and soak in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes. Squeeze the water out and add garlic, garlic salt and parsley flakes.
Mash everything together, then add olive oil, a teaspoon at a time, until the mixture becomes a paste.
This can be put on toasted Italian bread and used as garlic bread.
This spread provides a very strong garlic flavor with very little calories or fat.

title: pistachio pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk according to pkg. directions. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread second 1/2 Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Sprinkle with almonds and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: my mother's popcorn balls(great for halloween)
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together until brittle ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and pour over popcorn. Mix well.
Wet hands in cold water and shape into balls.
Wrap balls in waxed paper or plastic see-through wrap.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove and finely chop mushroom stems.
Combine dressing, bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and chopped mushroom stems in medium bowl.

title: double treat cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and peanut butter until creamy. Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Add vanilla and chocolate chips. Stir until mixed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: deluxe macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Note:
If using turkey bacon, you will need 1 tablespoon canola or olive oil.

title: stuffed pasta with parmesan
directions: To
quarts
boiling salted water, add 1/2 tablespoon margarine.
Cook
stuffed
pasta
according
to
directions. Drain.
Place
in
a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Blend cream into sour cream; stir in half of Parmesan cheese, pepper, salt and nutmeg.
Pour over pasta; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: carol's chili rellenos
directions: Drain chillies and take seeds out.
Rinse well and air dry. Beat milk and eggs together.
Layer in an 8 x 8-inch oiled pan.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Precook chicken in microwave in 8 x 10-inch dish.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Mix rest of ingredients and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gringa salsa(mild to medium)
directions: Empty cans of sauce in bowl.
Add 1/2 can water.
Squeeze juice from lime.
Chop or cut cilantro and mix in.
Chop tomatoes and onion and add.
Add 1/2 teaspoon each of garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and salt.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: apple rolls
directions: Mix together and chill for 2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes; drain well.
Cream with hand mixer, adding enough milk to make creamy.
Continue mixing, adding cream cheese, sour cream, butter, onion salt, salt and pepper.
Pour into ovenproof dish.
Top with Sauteed Mushrooms.
Add paprika as topping.
Cook at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and fried bacon slices together.
Add bite size pieces of broccoli.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top and refrigerate.
Can do ahead.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook dates, sugar and oleo, stirring constantly, until oleo is absorbed.
Add nuts and pour hot mixture over Rice Krispies in a large bowl; mix well. Form into small balls.
Put balls in a bag of powdered sugar; shake well.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: beets and pineapple
directions: Drain the canned beets.
Stir together the first ingredients. Add the lemon juice and beets.
Heat and serve.

title: rhubarb-raspberry pie
directions: Beat egg, flour, honey and jello together.
Add to cut up rhubarb.
Place between crusts in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: apple dip
directions: Dip apples in lemon juice to keep them from turning brown. Mix all ingredients together and chill.
It tastes like caramel apples.

title: applesauce walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pans.
Put dry cake mix, butter, applesauce, eggs and cinnamon into a large mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Stir in walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: delicious salad
directions: Dissolve jello and pull marshmallows apart and dissolve in hot jello.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Place in refrigerator. Let stay until starts to congeal, then stir in whipped cream. Return to refrigerator.
Let stay until congealed.
(Best to make night before.)

title: funruly salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in salad bowl.
Mix well; cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Place chicken on grill or rack of broiler pan.
Brush with half of sauce.
Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes; turn and brush with remaining sauce. Continue grilling or broiling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey apple salad
directions: In medium bowl, gently stir together turkey, apple, celery and raisins.
Be sure to break up chunks of turkey.
In another bowl, stir together salad dressing and brown sugar; pour over turkey mixture.
Toss gently to coat.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 1 1/2 cups or 2 servings.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well, chill. Makes 4 servings of about 190 calories each.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Store in covered container. Mix with 1 cup hot water.
Yields 16 cups.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: speed-o minestrone soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, bring the broth, water, tomatoes, basil and pepper to a boil over high heat.
Meanwhile, drain the beans in a colander; rinse under cold running water and drain well.
In a food processor, coarsely chop the onion, carrot and garlic.
Add the onion, carrot, garlic, drained beans, peas and macaroni to the boiling broth mixture.
Reduce the heat to medium-low; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the macaroni is al dente, about 12 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese on top.

title: chicken alla parmigiana
directions: Dip chicken in flour, then in egg/milk mixture and then in bread crumbs. Fry in a little bit of oil, browning lightly on both sides. Drain on paper towels and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. When chicken is done, place 1 to 2 tablespoons Nepolitana Sauce on each piece of chicken. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of sauce, then slice of Mozzarella (which should cover chicken piece) and then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Put under broiler just long enough to melt cheese. Serve.

title: split pea soup(low-fat)
directions: In a large saucepot or Dutch oven, bring peas, water, carrots, onions, garlic, celery and ham to a rapid boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and cook, covered, at a gently rolling boil, 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until peas are soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes to blend flavors.
In a blender or food processor, process 2 to 3 cups at a time, until pureed.
Return to saucepan and reheat if necessary.
Serves 10.
Freezes well.

title: fresh ice tea with vernors
directions: In large bowl, mix tea bags with hot water and squeezed lemons.
Add fresh mint and sugar.
Stir until tea is strong as desired and sweetened to taste.
Remove lemons, tea bags and fresh mint.
Add water as much as desired.
When cool, add Vernors. Strain.
Put in large pitcher.
Put in refrigerator until ready to drink and put ice in glass.
Add tea and squirt of lemon juice. Very good!

title: caramel morsel bars
directions: Melt
caramels	and
water
in	pan; stir until smooth. Pour over
cereal
and
nuts until well coated.	With greased fingers, press
into
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased).
Sprinkle morsels on top.
Place
in a 200° oven for 5 minutes.	Spread softened morsels.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Combine beef, bread, eggs, 1/2 cup onion, salt, pepper and water.
Pat out on waxed paper about 1/2 inch thick.
Combine 1/4 cup onion, carrots, fat and celery; spread over meat mixture.
Roll jelly roll fashion.
Place in roast pan.
Pour tomato juice over top and sides; add enough water to keep from burning or sticking in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabbage delight
directions: Cut cabbage into desired size. Cook cabbage and carrots until tender.
Pour into a large baking dish or oven pan.
Brown hamburger, onion, green pepper and mushrooms; drain.
Add seasoning.
Pour tomato juice and hamburger over cabbage.
Top with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven until tomato juice is hot and cheese melts.

title: dana's one dish meal
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic salt and drain.
Cook noodles until done.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, and put into large casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake in 375° oven until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with rolls or cornbread.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef then put in taco seasoning by package directions; set aside.
Mash avocado in 1 tablespoon mayonnaise; set aside.
Then layer in a large oblong pan as follows:
refried beans, ground beef, avocado, sour cream, lettuce, tomato, black olives and cheese.
Use Doritos to dip.

title: troy aikman cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire and finely chopped beef and onions.
Food processor or blender works well.
Spread mix on flat tortillas.
Roll up like burritos.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Serve with salsa for dipping.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Slice 2 of the eggs into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add milk all a once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir sausage and corn into sauce; pour over eggs.
Slice remaining eggs; arrange atop mixture.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry treats(candy)
directions: Put sauce on low heat.
Add jello.
Mix and stir well to dissolve. Add sugar and mix well until dissolved.
Bring to an even boil.
Remove from fire and add nuts. Pour into buttered pan. Let stand overnight. Cut into squares and shake in sack of powdered sugar to coat.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix oleo, cream cheese and confectioners sugar in small bowl; set aside.
In large bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Add whipped topping.
Then add cream cheese mixture to pudding.
Place cookie crumbs in container 1/2-inch thick.
Alternate cookies and cream mixture until container is full.
Finish with 1/2 cup of cookie crumbs; chill at least 6 hours.

title: laura and rachel's fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer. Pour into pie crust. Bake for 45 minutes at 325. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: never fail gingerbread
directions: Cream the molasses, sugar, egg and butter. Blend well.
Sift flour, cinnamon and ginger. Fold into molasses and mix well. Last, add cup of boiling water and soda.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: asparagus and swiss cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie crust.
Prick bottom and side of pastry.
Bake 10 minutes; prick again and let cool.
Reduce to 375°.
Boil asparagus until tender.
Drain and dry on paper towel.
Put in blender the cream, eggs, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in cheese and Swiss cheese.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle 3/4 grated cheese on top.
Return to oven for 3 minutes.

title: three-bean salad with honey-mustard dressing(serves 8)
directions: In a large bowl mix the beans and tomatoes.
In a blender, combine the oil, mustard, water, basil, honey and pepper. Sprinkle with the chives.
Toss well.

title: dream pie
directions: Drain oranges; mix Cool Whip and milk.
Stir in lemon juice and oranges.
Pour into graham cracker crust or lime bowl with vanilla wafers.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cut up fresh fruit (strawberries, watermelon, grapes, pineapple, banana, cantaloupe, etc.).
Dip bananas in pineapple juice to keep from being brown.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix together.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Then turn down oven to 300° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: glori-fried pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops in 2 tablespoons shortening.

Pour off fat. Stir in soup and water. Cover and cook over low heat (210° to 220°, electric frying pan) for 45 minutes or until tender. Stir now and then. Make gravy with leftover soup and water. Serve on boiled potatoes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake at 350°.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage and onion, add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler no. 2
directions: Heat sugar, peaches and cornstarch in a pan until warm.
Pour in pie plate with crust.
Add butter and lemon.
Add top pie crust to pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove skin from salmon and flake.
Add beaten eggs and milk to salmon.
Then add salt, pepper and cracker crumbs.
Makes 6 patties.
Brown in frying pan with Pam spray.
Serve with mashed potatoes and fresh peas or broccoli.

title: hershey cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs thoroughly, one at a time. Add flour and syrup alternately, blending after each addition. Add vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma jones' old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together until creamed.
Add egg and milk; beat.
Add dry ingredients to mix.
Add hot water after well mixed.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch prepared pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and make a well in middle.
Add liquids in order listed.
Bake in 4 (1 pound) coffee cans (grease and flour well).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together, adding bananas last.
Freeze.
May be used as a salad or dessert.

title: curried shrimp
directions: About 35 minutes before serving, shell and devein shrimp.
In small bowl, combine shrimp, salt, cornstarch, ginger, pepper and sugar.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook onion until tender, but not brown.
Stir in curry powder. Cook 1 minute.
Turn heat to high and add shrimp mixture.
Cook just until shrimp turn pink and are tender.
Serve with cocktail picks.
Makes 8 appetizer servings.
Each serving has about 120 calories.

title: meat loaf pinwheels
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, half of cheese spread, egg and salt.
Mix lightly.
Pat out meat mixture to cover 10 x 12-inch rectangle of foil.
Combine remaining rice and parsley; spread out over meat. Roll up starting at narrow end and wrap securely; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut roll into eight slices.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until meat is done.
Yields 8 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method.
Mix flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Stir in.
Form into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll balls in mixture of the 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: corn-crisped chicken
directions: Roll chicken in evaporated milk, "thin" milk just won't do. Then roll "wet" chicken into corn flake mixture.
Place in shallow baking pan lined with foil.
Do not cover.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: swiss chocolate delight cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in 3 well-greased and floured cake pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Then stir in milk.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: In advance, peel, seed and finely dice 1 cucumber.
Peel and finely chop half the onion.
Seed and sliver 1 green pepper. Peel, quarter and squeeze out seeds and chop 6 of the tomatoes. Mince the garlic.

title: rio grande spinach salad
directions: Clean spinach well and tear into small pieces.
Cut tomato in wedges and arrange over spinach.
Cut eggs in quarters and arrange over top.
Cut onion into slices and separate into rings over spinach.
Crumble Feta cheese over all.
Shake olive oil, vinegar, oregano and pepper in small jar and drizzle over salad.
Sprinkle with olive slices.
Toss and serve.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven at 425°.
Melt shortening in large iron skillet until sizzling.
Stir all remaining ingredients together except water. Thin mixture slowly with water until runny.
Pour into hot grease.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: curt's peanut clusters
directions: Melt milk chocolate chips and peanut butter chips in the microwave for 45 seconds to 2 minutes until well blended.
Remove from microwave and add dry roasted peanuts.
Drop onto waxed paper and let set in the refrigerator.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Combine brown sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan, stirring well; add remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 15 minutes, stirring often.
Serve with ham.
Yields 1 cup.

title: holiday ham spread
directions: Combine ham, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, onion, sweet pickle relish and 4 ounces of cream cheese; chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add milk and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: baked chicken with wine sauce
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of casserole dish. Place Swiss cheese on top of chicken to cover.
Mix white wine and can of soup together, then spread on top of cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over soup mixture, covering the entire dish.
Drizzle melted butter on top of bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: tasty salmon spread
directions: Drain, flake and clean salmon.
Combine all ingredients (except pecans and parsley).
Shape into 2 balls or loaves on wax paper.
Wrap and chill for several hours.
Roll chilled balls or loaves in parsley and pecan mixture.
For serving, turn out onto a dish and serve with assortment of crackers or fresh vegetables. This is a delicious spread! My daughter grave me the recipe.
She serves it often to her guests in California.

title: bohemian punch
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot; bring to boil, then simmer.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions and drain grease.
Add all other ingredients except biscuits.
Pour in casserole dish and bake in oven at 350° until it begins to bubble.
Take out and add biscuits on top.
Bake until biscuits are done.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Bone and skin chicken.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Place cheese slices on chicken. Add 1/2 cup water to soup.
Pour over chicken. Add melted butter to stuffing mix. Cover chicken with stuffing. Cover dish and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Cook package of pudding as directed.
Blend dry cake mix into hot pudding.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 30-35 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs singly, beating well. Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Add raisins. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: poor woman's chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add coffee and vanilla; mix.
Add shortening last.
Mix well.
Put in 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: japanese pie
directions: Add in order.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cut cheese in chunks and melt.
When cheese is melted, add meat, chili, salsa and milk.
Cook on low in crock-pot for about 1 hour.
Buy 1 large bag tortilla chips and yum, yum.

title: lila's "homemade" biscuits
directions: Grease a pan or cookie sheet lavishly with butter (lots of butter).
Sprinkle with lots of Parmesan cheese (on top of the butter).
Open a can of Pillsbury buttermilk biscuits.
Plop into the pan or on the cookie sheet.
Turn biscuits over and coat on both sides.
Follow directions on the can for baking.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar, then one egg at a time.
Mix well after each.
Add milk, then cake flour, baking powder, vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: famous potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and enjoy.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar.
Stir in vanilla and salt. Add flour gradually.
Work in nuts thoroughly.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Form 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough should be set, but not brown.
Roll while warm in sifted powdered sugar.
Cool, then roll in powdered sugar again.

title: 3-layer quick method cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in mixing bowl. Add butter or Crisco and 1/2 of milk.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, additional milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in three layers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop pimento and water chestnuts. Mix all ingredients together. Serve with bread cubes or crackers.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix in corn flakes, oats, coconut and pecans.
Dough will be crumbly.
Make little balls and press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Leave on sheets a few minutes. Remove.

title: apricot pie
directions: In bowl sprinkle apricots with lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add sugar mixture to apricots, toss and mix. Fill pie crust, dot with butter.
Seal and flute edge.
Cover edge with foil.
Bake 370° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 20-25 minutes until crust is golden.
Cool on wire rack.

title: porcupines
directions: *May use any combination or single ground meat.

title: sausage cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
If mixture is too thick, add a little more milk.
Spray miniature muffin tins with Pam.
Fill with batter to 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 10-15 minutes.
Makes 10-12 muffins.

title: mexican rice
directions: Heat oil in heavy frying pan over medium heat. Add onion, garlic, rice and red pepper. Saute until onion is limp and rice opaque.
Add salt, cayenne, water and chicken broth granules. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Add peas and carrots and tomato.
Cook, stirring, just until vegetables are heated through. Serve rice immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach hors d'oeuvre
directions: Mix eggs and margarine together.
Add all other ingredients. Make into small patties like cookies.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until just to the point of becoming tender. Drain.
To the potatoes, add diced onion, bacon bits, Velveeta cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix together well.
Place in a baking casserole dish and bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: fried tater combo
directions: Prepare vegetables by chopping all into large bowl.
Coat with flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat oil in skillet at medium-high and put vegetables into hot oil, trying not to include excess flour.
Cook until brown and vegetables are tender.

title: stir-n-drop oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into bowl.
Add brown sugar and oats.
Mix in thoroughly oil, milk and eggs.
Add raisins (can use nuts, if preferred). Drop with teaspoon, 2 inches apart, on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, just until light touch with finger leaves no imprint.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: fancy sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, 1 cup sugar, milk, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Blend well by hand or mixer.
Pour into baking dish.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef.
Drain, then stir in taco seasoning, water and olives.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Separate crescents and arrange in a 9-inch pan to form crust.
Crush tortilla chips and cover crescents in pan.
Spoon meat mixture on top of tortilla chips.
Spread sour cream over meat.
Top with cheese and a few chip crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: "good as a restaurant's" chocolate mousse cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) round baking pans.
In large bowl, combine sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. With electric mixer at medium speed beat 2 minutes.
With spoon, stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire racks.
Remove from pans after about 10 minutes and continue cooling on racks.
Prepare Mousse Frosting and use it to fill and frost cooled cake.
Refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form balls.
Chill overnight or until firm.
Roll in chopped nuts or parsley.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter or oleo in baking dish.
Combine flour with 3/4 cup sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour fruit over batter, with juice; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ruby's camp cookies
directions: Cream and soften butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add the oatmeal and all other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate striped delight
directions: Mix crushed cookies and margarine in medium bowl.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons of milk until smooth.
Gently stir in 1 1/4 cups whipped topping; spread over crust.
Pour 3 1/4 cups of milk into large bowl, then add pudding mixes.
Beat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Add bouillon cubes to the tomato juice.
Add the small head shredded cabbage. Cook until tender. Add can of mixed vegetables. Continue cooking until tender and heated through.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
Miracle
Whip, vinegar and bacon. Blend Miracle Whip
and vinegar and add this sauce and bacon just before serving.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Melt margarine and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over pecans and stir until covered.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind or chop fine the apples, oranges and lemon.
Mix with cranberries and add sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Refrigerate overnight so flavors will blend before serving.

title: zesty sausage and rice
directions: Combine sausage, rice and 1 1/2 cups water in medium saucepan. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Add vegetables, red pepper and salsa; cover and simmer 5 minutes longer. Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: lemon apricot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg whites, which are beaten stiff and fold into cake batter.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish and set aside. Combine the next ingredients and sprinkle over sweet potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 10 servings. (Sometimes I experiment with other extracts and add a trace of nutmeg.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: teatime tassies
directions: Mix together the softened cream cheese and margarine.
Stir in flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls; press in small muffin cups.
Beat together the egg, brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix in half of pecans.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture in cups.
Sprinkle with rest of pecans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Makes 24.

title: nectarine-lemon spritz
directions: Combine all ingredients, except honey and sugar for glasses. Chill for 2 hours.
Dip rims of glasses in the honey and sprinkle with sugar.
Serves 3 people.

title: creamy chicken manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti; drain well.
Stir together sour cream and cheese until smooth in large bowl.
Add chicken, drained mushrooms, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Spoon mixture into manicotti.
Arrange in single layer in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine Velveeta and milk and heat thoroughly.
Stir often until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour over manicotti and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and scramble hamburger and drain.
Put taco seasoning on meat.
Heat oven to 350°.
Line rectangular pan with corn tortillas.
In separate bowl, mix soup, beans and tomato sauce together.
Pour over corn tortillas.
Cover with seasoned meat. Cover top with cheese.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: herbed rice
directions: Cook rice and onion in butter until tender.
Add seasonings and cook 1 minute.
Add broth, bring to boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy cabbage soup
directions: Heat 2 cups of water to boiling in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add cabbage, celery and onion.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Boil until tender, about 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Place in blender container. Cover and blend until of uniform consistency.

title: mexican delight candy
directions: In large pot, bring to boil 2 1/2 cups sugar, milk, oleo, salt and soda.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to the sugar mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until thick.
Drop on wax paper, one spoonful at a time.

title: filling for lane cake
directions: Chop or grind raisins, coconut and nuts; set aside.
Beat egg yolks; stir in sugar and butter.
Cook over double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
When done and still hot, put in rest of ingredients.
Spread layers and on top and sides.
Let set until cool or cold.
Cover with white icing.

title: microwave stuffed green peppers
directions: In medium glass bowl, crumble ground beef; stir in onions. Heat 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes on High until beef is brown, stirring once; drain.
Stir in 1 can tomato sauce, water, 1 tablespoon cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat, covered, 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes on High. Stir in rice; let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and rinse.
Spoon beef-rice filling into each half; place in oblong baking dish. Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Heat, covered, 10 to 12 minutes on High until peppers are tender.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: rocky road pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat margarine until softened.
Add sugar and brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually beat in flour.
Spread dough evenly in an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake about 12 minutes or until golden.
Sprinkle peanuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips onto hot crust.
Return pizza to oven about 6 to 8 minutes more, until marshmallows are golden.
Cool in pan on cooling rack.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: stuffed tomatoes, sicilian style
directions: Cut off the tops of the peeled tomatoes and remove most of the interior meat with a melon scoop, shaking out the seeds and juice.

title: lemon broccoli
directions: Trim broccoli. Separate into flowerets.
Cook in a small amount of boiling water until tender-crisp. Drain. Reserve the flowerets and keep warm.
Saute onions in butter and oil over medium heat (2 minutes). Remove from heat. Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Return broccoli to saucepan.
Stir gently to coat with lemon mixture.

title: springtime carrot cake
directions: Combine salad oil, sugar, hot water and egg yolks.
Beat on low speed of mixer until well blended.
Do not overbeat.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt. Alternately add liquid ingredients, carrots and nuts to dry ingredients, blending well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cake batter.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) cake pans and bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes or until well done.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: To your favorite pie crust add grated onion; roll it out and bake.
Melt butter in a skillet and brown beef; add salt and pepper.
Put it into pie shell and top with cheese slices.
Broil until cheese is melted and serve at once.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all in a bowl; mix well with spoon.
Spread in pan. Bake at 375° for no longer than 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter chewy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt peanut butter and margarine in microwave.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Beat in milk and vanilla.
Serve cold in tall glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 1 serving.

title: salad dressing a la doro's
directions: Blend all ingredients and gently whisk in oil.
Whisk for a minute or 2 until completely blended.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Combine jello with hot water; let set and whip.
Add mayonnaise.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: dirt cake
directions: Process cookies in blender until crushed.
Combine softened cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar in mixer bowl.
Mix well.
Combine milk and pudding and mix in large bowl.
Mix until thickened.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x13 as directed on box.

title: colorado sunshine jello salad
directions: Make a tossed salad using lettuce, tomatoes, scallions, bell pepper, cucumber, radishes, carrots, etc.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: *Or put 1 teaspoon baking powder in 1 1/2 cups flour.

title: charcoal steaks
directions: Marinate steaks with soy sauce and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Use fork with sharp tines to pierce meat, about a quarter of an inch as you sprinkle soy sauce on so it will penetrate meat. Let marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Get charcoal hot.
Add small amount of water soaked hickory chips. Cook steaks, covered, to desired doneness.

title: waldorf chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the chicken, apples, celery and raisins.
In a cup, stir together the mayonnaise, yogurt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to the chicken mixture and toss until coated. Season to taste with pepper.
Serve on lettuce-lined salad plates.

title: egg and cheese souffle
directions: In a greased 9 x 12-inch pan, cover bottom with bread (crust removed).
Add a layer of ham, then sprinkle cheese over all.
Top with another layer of bread (crust removed).
Beat together and pour over layers the eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: bacon-water chestnut roll-ups
directions: Drain water chestnuts and marinate them in soy sauce at least 1 hour.
Cut bacon slices into thirds.
Roll 2 or 3 water chestnuts up in the bacon and fasten with toothpick.
Coat the bacon roll-up in brown sugar.
Cover cookie sheet with foil for easy clean up.
Place roll-ups on cookie sheet and bake at 400° until the bacon is done.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients in unbaked pie shell.
Cook for 1 hour at 325°.

title: barbeque sauce(for 1 chicken)
directions: Melt oleo and add
all
other
ingredients.
Heat. Baste chicken each time it is turned to cook on grill.

title: autumn chowder
directions: In a saucepan, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp; remove to paper towels. Drain, reserving 1 teaspoon drippings. In the drippings, saute onion until tender. Add the potato, carrot, water and bouillon. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until the vegetables are almost tender. Stir in the milk, corn and pepper. Cook 5 minutes longer. Combine the flour and cold water until smooth; gradually whisk into soup. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened. Remove from the heat; stir in cheese until melted. Sprinkle the bacon.

title: flavored milk shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Blend about 1 minute, until smooth and frothy.
Makes 1 or 2 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine, melted. Pack into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the eggs, margarine and powdered sugar together for no less than 15 minutes.
Spread this over the unbaked crumb crust.
Add sliced bananas and pineapple.
Add layer of whipped topping.
Top with cherries and pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 15 to 16 large servings.

title: family or fruit pies
directions: Melt butter in oblong glass dish.
Mix together, with mixer, all ingredients, except fruit.
Pour over batter.
Add fruit on top (cherries are real good).
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serve.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Soften butter.
Add preserves and mix thoroughly.
Serve with warm breads.

title: broccoli cheese rice casserole
directions: Precook broccoli and mix all ingredients in large pot or nonstick frying pan on low until cheese melts and all is hot.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Prick each hot dog with a fork.
Place hot dogs in greased casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over hot dogs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add flour and milk.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: debose's sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets. Remove skins. Cream while hot. Add butter, sugar, baking powder, eggs and vanilla; beat well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: alice's pickled kielbasi from maine
directions: Cut up kielbasi into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix rest of ingredients together and heat a few minutes.
Put meat into clean glass jar and cover with warm liquid.
Cool, cover jar and place into refrigerator.

title: cantaloupe turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey, cantaloupe, celery and green onion.
In small bowl, mix oil, vinegar, oil, mustard, soy sauce, red pepper flakes and garlic.
Combine mixture with turkey/cantaloupe mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place the apples in a greased 9 inch pie dish.
In a bowl, combine sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon, and allspice; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, flour and baking soda.
Add egg, margarine, sugar and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, combine rice mix, canned soups and water.
Place chicken breasts over mixture. Sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Drizzle with margarine.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and then add mayonnaise and soup. Spread mixture in large casserole dish (13 x 9-inch).
Add topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spinach dip in french bread
directions: Slice lid off bread and hollow out insides.
Cut these into 1-inch cubes.
Mix ingredients and chill until ready to serve. Put in bread and serve with bread cubes.

title: alpine cake
directions: Put marshmallows in bowl and pour water over them - mix, then add condensed milk, chopped nuts and dates - then blend together.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Mix broccoli and Velveeta; spoon into greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs; dot with margarine.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate.
Combine with brown sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough in powdered sugar; roll to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in bowl.
Heat margarine, cocoa and Coca-Cola to boiling point.
Pour over flour mixture.
Mix soda into buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until it is cooled slightly before adding eggs, vanilla, salt and marshmallows will float.
Pour into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 cup Bundt pan. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Combine milk and egg. Beat with fork in shallow dish.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then coat with flour mixture.
Place on roasting pan, foil lined. Drizzle butter over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
(I use 3 breasts, 3 thighs and 3 legs.)

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Add first 5 ingredients and cook until tender, approximately 1 hour.
Add soup and cheese. Simmer 15 minutes and enjoy!

title: incredible icing
directions: Mix well until creamy and sugar is blended (not gritty), about 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut and kielbasa
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, heat Wesson oil.
Wash and drain sauerkraut.
Put it in oil.
Cut in small pieces (rounds) the kielbasa.
Put over sauerkraut and caraway seed.
Cook on low heat for about 10 minutes.

title: sophisticated meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into small balls and brown.
Remove balls from skillet.
Pour off drippings and stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended and heat.
Serve meatballs over a platter of hot noodles.
Pour sauce on top.

title: mock crab dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with slivered almonds.

title: fiesta chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken in juice, garlic and seasonings 15 minutes. Cook chicken in oil 2 to 3 minutes or until chicken loses pink color.
Add onion and peppers.
Continue cooking 3 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir in salsa.
Spoon onto tortillas. Top with cheese.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cook ground beef with onion, drain.
Mix everything together in crock pot and cook on low for 3 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: barbecued muskrat
directions: Remove muskrat pieces in shallow, foil-lined pan.
Make sauce from remaining ingredients and brush on pieces.
Pour remaining sauce in bottom of pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 90
minutes or until tender, basting every 15 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Bring oleo, sugar, syrup and canned milk to a boil in a skillet. Cook 3 1/2 minutes. Add cocoa, vanilla and nuts. Pour in pan and let set up.
Cut into squares.

title: german oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cookies sit for 1 minute on cookie sheet if they are too soft to remove.

title: nancy harkin's cheesecake
directions: Cream in large bowl soft cream cheese and sour cream, mix in sugar, flour and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth. Separate eggs.
Add beaten egg yolks a little at a time to cheese mixture and beat.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Pies will be done when they look slick on top.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar in food processor fitted with steel blade.
Scatter butter pieces over flour mixture, tossing to coat butter with a little flour.
Cut butter into flour with five 1-second pulses.
Add shortening and continue cutting in until flour is pale yellow and resembles coarse cornmeal with butter bits no larger than small peas, about four more 1-second pulses.
Turn mixture into medium bowl.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Sift together dry ingredients (except brown sugar).
Add beaten egg and mix until it has a fine, crumblike texture.
Add fruit cocktail; mix thoroughly.
Pour into large 10-inch buttered pie pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and walnuts to taste.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: grilled doves
directions: Mix oil, garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Brush over both sides of the birds.
Grill or broil 4 to 5-inches from heat for 7 to 8 minutes to the side, basting several times with the oil mixture.

title: syrup
directions: Put sugar and a little of the dry Kool-Aid mix in a small saucepan.
Stir it together then add water.
(Amount of water you add depends on how thick and sweet you want your syrup.)
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and syrup starts to thicken a little.

title: chicken & broccoli braid
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Mix all filling ingredients. Unroll crescent rolls. Do not separate. Arrange on 12 x 15 inch pan; roll to edges. On longest sides, cut dough into strips 1 1/2 inches apart, 3 inches deep using a pizza cutter. Leave 6 inches in center for filling. Spread filling in middle. Lift strips of dough across mixture to meet in center, twisting each strip one turn. Tuck ends up to form a braid.
Brush with egg white over dough. Bake 25-28 minutes or until deep golden brown.
10 Servings.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix and pour
into
a 9 x 13-inch pan.	Let chill until firm.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: While mixing other ingredients, put cabbage in very hot water to soften for easy rolling.
In separate bowl, mix 1 can tomato paste, salt, pepper, a little sugar and enough water to come up to level of cabbage.
Put meat and rice mixture on cabbage and roll. Pour tomato paste mixture over rolls and cook very slowly for 2 hours and 15 minutes.
Never stack cabbage more than 2 deep.

title: two layer cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add eggs, one at a time.
Add cake flour and milk.
Mix.
Add vanilla or coconut flavoring. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dumplings for soup
directions: Combine water and butter in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; add pancake mix, parsley and garlic, stirring vigorously until mixture leaves side of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Drop tablespoon on soup. Cook about 2 minutes or until they come to the top.

title: crepes with chocolate and raspberry
directions: Make crepes according to directions.
The thinner the better. Make about 2 per person.
Once the crepes are cooked (this can be done in advance), sprinkle the whole crepe with the chocolate and spread the jam evenly over the crepe.
Roll the crepe, or fold into triangle, with some jam "over-flowing".

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt margarine or butter in pan.
Add sugar, egg, dates and pecans.
Cook on low heat until it boils.
Take off heat and stir in Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Let cool.
Form into balls.	Roll in coconut.
Makes 55.

title: steak diane
directions: Slice the filet into thin strips, making sure to cut against the grain of the meat.
Lay the sliced meat out flat.
Cut the lemon in half and set one half aside.
Squeeze the other half over the meat and pat so that all pieces are damp with lemon juice. Sprinkle the granulated garlic and the pepper evenly on the meat. Set meat aside for 10 minutes.
Cut remaining lemon half into thin slices.
Bring remaining ingredients to a simmer over high heat in a large saucepan.
Add lemon slices, meat and optional ingredients (except toast).
Saute for 3 to 5 minutes or until meat is done to your liking.
Arrange the meat on toast slices and pour sauce over the top.
Serve with a baked potato.

title: potiron au gratin (french)(pumpkin au gratin)
directions: Thoroughly combine the pumpkin, salt, pepper, nutmeg, cloves and butter.
Place in a small lightly buttered casserole. Beat egg lightly and mix in cream and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over pumpkin gently.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes or until top is puffed and lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: twinkie cake(children's recipe)
directions: (Children may need help with slicing.)

title: chicken creole
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium high heat until hot.
Add onions, celery, green pepper, garlic and carrots.
Saute until crisp-tender.
Add tomato soup with mushrooms.
Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken.
Put in slow cooker and cook for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve over cooked rice sprinkled with parsley.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Grind cookies and set aside.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix pudding according to package directions, using 3 cups milk.
Add to cheese mixture.
Fold in along with Cool Whip and vanilla.

title: teenager's delight
directions: Brown meat and onion with salt.
Drain and put in large casserole dish.
Layer with Tater Tots.
Mix milk and soup and pour over Tots.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover, sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Then sprinkle with onion rings and bake for 5 minutes more.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix
and bake at 350° about 40 minutes in 2 unbaked pie crusts.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Chop half of mushrooms thinly; slice remaining mushrooms. Melt butter in 5 or 6-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add chopped mushrooms, onion and thyme.
Stir often until lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix flour with vegetables; pour into blender or food processor and whirl, adding as much broth as needed to smoothly puree mixture.
Pour mixture back into pan, adding remaining broth, sliced mushrooms, bay leaf and cream. Bring to boil on high heat.
Reduce heat to low; simmer to blend flavors about 10 minutes.
Add sherry if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick mushroom soup
directions: Saute 1 box sliced mushrooms and a chopped onion in butter. Add chicken broth.
When warm, add 1 pint sour cream, salt and pepper to taste and paprika.

title: trifle
directions: Make custard (I use Bird's custard powder) with 1 pint of milk.
Let it cool, cover with wrap to stop skin forming.
Cut sponge cakes into thick slices.
Put into dish and add defrosted raspberries and macaroons.
Pour over wine mixed with milk adding more sherry as necessary to soak the cakes thoroughly.
Sprinkle with lemon rind.
Add the almonds and cover with cooled custard. Beat cream and egg whites together until stiff.
Sweeten to taste and pile on top of custard.

title: macadamia nut chicken liver spread
directions: Bring salted water to a boil.
Put the chicken livers into the pan and simmer about 5 minutes.
Drain and mash livers.
Put them through a food mill.
Add the other ingredients and chill.

title: cowboy beans
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon over medium-high heat until crisp.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
heat to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and add to chicken broth.
I use chicken bouillon cubes (2 cubes per 1 cup of water).
Saute chopped onion in butter until clear.
Add to broccoli and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil, add cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Can cook this in crock-pot for several hours.

title: creamy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, sugar, milk, margarine and salt. Bring to a full boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add milk chocolate morsels and semi-sweet morsels.
Stir until melted and well blended.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into aluminum foil lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill
2 hours.

title: pulled mints
directions: Put sugar, water and butter in a saucepan.
Without stirring, cook until a little of the boiling syrup dropped in cold water makes a hard ball or is brittle.
Flavor with 5 to 10 drops of oil of peppermint or to suit taste and pour out on a marble slab or platter.
When cool, pull until light.
Make a long roll and cut into cubes with scissors or cut into finger length pieces.
Fold 2 ends together and cut across the center.
This will give a twisted effect and make the right size.
When candy is cut, put in a tightly closed tin box and leave for 8 to 10 hours to cream.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break into pieces the eight slices of bread and layer into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer half of the cheese, half of the meat, half of the cheese and the other half of the meat.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread nuts in pan; spread coconut over top of nuts.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Cream together the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Combine and spread over cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: make ahead noodles
directions: Measure all ingredients into plastic bag or airtight container.
Store for up to 2 months.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes (do not overcook).
Cook and coarsely grate potatoes.
Melt butter and add cheese.
Stir in sour cream. Combine everything and pour in greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot-apple bake
directions: Put 1/2 carrots and apples in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and put 1/2 on top.
Repeat.
Pour orange juice on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake until firm.

title: jo's macaroni casserole delight
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Put in buttered casserole.
Saute celery in butter.
Add to macaroni.
Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper; drain and add on top of celery.
Sprinkle half of cheese over meat layer.
Spread can of soup over cheese.
Add tomatoes on top of cheese and sprinkle the last half of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered and 15 more minutes, uncovered.

title: new west chicken salad
directions: Cut grapes in half.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: easy slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and use a good slaw dressing when ready to serve.

title: shrimp or lobster ball
directions: Mix ingredients; cheese just room temperature.
Shape.
May roll ball in chopped parsley or bacon bits.
Chill 2 hours.

title: red punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Chill.
To serve, add ginger ale, stirring well.
Yields 4 1/2 quarts. This makes a great Christmas punch.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 32 cupcakes; bake
for 20 minutes.

title: chili meat balls
directions: Combine 1/2 of onion, salt and pepper and all of the meat. Make the meat balls; brown them in the Wesson oil with the remaining onion and green pepper.
Drain off the fat.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Add tomato sauce; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If it's dry, add 1 cup tomatoes or another can of sauce.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and make a well. Add eggs and milk. Mix with hands. If too sticky, add flour. Wrap in foil and let set for 30 minutes. Roll out thin.

title: glaze for strawberry cake
directions: If frozen berries are used, drain well and blot with paper towel.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over top of cake. Allow to run down the sides.
If making layer cakes, spread glaze between layers.

title: black olive bread
directions: Make a spread by mixing olives, onions, cheese and enough dressing to make a paste. Spread paste on French bread that has been sliced face open. Spread paste evenly over one side of the bread. Place top of the bread and bake at 375° until bread is browned. Slice into 2-inch slices or little squares.

title: chili con queso(mexican cheese dip)
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble; reserve.
Remove all grease from skillet, except enough to coat the bottom (about 2 tablespoons).
Saute onion and green pepper over medium heat in same skillet until softened and beginning to brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in desired amount of cherry peppers (I use about 6 to 8 for noticeable heat) and chopped tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low.

title: wesson oil buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and Wesson oil together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift baking powder and soda with flour.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in 350° oven until cakes are light brown.

title: fastest lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade or limeade with sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in whipped topping.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: pizza turnovers
directions: Saute mushrooms, green pepper and onion in margarine.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasoning; simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
On lightly floured board, roll pastry to 1/8-inch thickness; cut into 3 1/2-inch rounds.
Spoon 1 teaspoon mixture on center of each round.
Fold in half; press edges together with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add melted butter, beaten eggs and milk.
Stir.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Put into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package; drain well and squeeze to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape spinach mixture into 1-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Spinach balls may be made days in advance and frozen.) Makes 10 dozen.

title: "goop"
directions: Gradually add starch to glue.
Add tempera paint or food coloring for color.
If too gooey, add more starch.
Store in a plastic bag.
Use often and it will last a long time.

title: microwave chunky peanut butter cups
