directions: In a small bowl, combine filling ingredients; stir well until mixture forms a ball (for easier handling, refrigerate 1 hour). Shape into balls, using 1/2 teaspoon of mixture for each.

title: limeade pie
directions: Beat limeade, Eagle Brand milk and food coloring.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer chopped broccoli in a casserole dish.
Add 1 can of celery soup over the top of the broccoli.
Add the melted margarine into the bread cubes and stir until well moistened.
Add this to the top of the soup.
Continue to layer, broccoli, soup and bread mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, or in a microwave oven for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook with onion in small amount of water. Drain.
Add cracker crumbs, butter and almost all of cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Beat eggs slightly, then add milk.
Mix with squash mixture.
Pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 425°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix the flour and Crisco until lumpy.
Stir egg, salt and sugar together and add enough water to make the cup full.
Add to flour mixture and mix slightly until dough is ready to roll into pie crust form.
Pinch off amount needed for pie tin to be used and roll out on floured board or cloth and place in pie pan. Freezes well.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine the pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
To dry ingredients, add pumpkin mixture along with soda dissolved in milk.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Mix dressing and add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Cover top with catsup and return to oven and bake another 30 minutes.
You may bake with bacon strips on top, if you like.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind all ingredients together and mix with 1/2 bottle chili sauce.
Spread onto one half of hamburger bun and put under the broiler until the cheese melts.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients except water.
May make the full amount with 6 quarts of water, or add teaspoons of mixture in 1 cup hot water.
Add mixture to taste.

title: maraschino cherry candy
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll
dough
around
a maraschino cherry. Roll into a smooth ball in palms.
Dip into melting chocolate. Let harden.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach in lukewarm water.
Wrap well and chill in refrigerator to crisp.
Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and mustard; beat until dressing is thick and syrupy and sugar is dissolved.
Tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Add the bacon, water chestnuts and 4 of the boiled eggs (chopped).
Pour dressing over all; let stand 1/2 hour.
Slice remaining eggs and use to garnish top of salad.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Mix and let stand overnight, then roll, cut and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tuna crunch
directions: Save 1/2 cup noodles.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining noodles and cashews on and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: meat balls and spaghetti
directions: Soften bread in milk.
Add eggs, salt, flour and onion.
Add to meat; mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Put tomato juice in pan; bring to boil.
Add balls; cook on medium for 10 minutes, then simmer for 1 hour.
Add cooked spaghetti.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well and pour over lettuce salad.

title: pork chop stew
directions: Brown pork chops (in Crisco) on both sides in skillet.
Peel and cut up potatoes.
Put around edges of skillet between and under pork chops.
Add celery, green pepper and onions.
Add oregano to tomato juice and pour over chops and potatoes.
(Try to cover potatoes with sauce.) Cover skillet and simmer on low 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling evenly in baking dish.
Pour pineapple over filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Pour margarine evenly over layer.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rich crescent dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour. Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 30 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add egg. Beat well. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Stir in candied fruit and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: vegetable gumbo
directions: Let meat and seasonings cook until tender, then add the remaining ingredients.
Cook slow.
Keep lid on until done.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients; sift together three times. Combine milk, vanilla and butter.
Add to dry ingredients, beat until smooth.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spread in a buttered 6-cup casserole.
Mix brown sugar and cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook and cool macaroni shells.
Combine Italian dressing and milk.
Pour over macaroni, chicken and vegetables.
This is great as a meal in itself.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cheese and sugar until light.
Add salt and flavorings; beat.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each.
Add flour; mix.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Mix pumpkin, eggs, oil and water well.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time.
Stir in pecans.
Grease and flour 1 loaf pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken elastic
directions: Pick meat off bones when cooled.
If necessary, cut in bite size pieces. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a good size casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: anisplatzchen
directions: Beat eggs in mixture until fluffy.
Add sugar beating continuously for 20 minutes.
Add dry ingredients, beat another 3 minutes.
Add anise seed.
Drop onto well-greased and floured cookie sheet and form a round cookie by swirling dough with spoon. Let stand to dry 8 hours or overnight.
Bake in 325° oven about 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: egg rolls
directions: Precook celery 5 to 6 minutes in boiling water, drain and mash. Brown green onion, mushrooms, bean sprouts and garlic.
Add water chestnuts, shrimp, chicken, chicken broth, soy sauce and sesame seed.
Heat.
If too watery, add 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Let mixture cool.
Spoon into square skins then fold in sides and then end.
Mix egg with fork and spoon on remaining end.
Glue into rest of skin.
Fry until brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: For a 9-inch pie plate, make crust by crushing the graham crackers; mix with the melted oleo and sugar.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together. Let rise in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight. Roll out and let rise about 2 1/2 hours. Don't work too much flour into them. Kind of sticky when putting on board. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cheesy corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased iron frying pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat egg whites until stiff; set aside. Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar; beat until smooth. Add eggs to creamed mixture and mix well.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Add egg whites and vanilla.

title: easy macaroons
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove to rack.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic, onion and anchovies in Wesson oil and melted butter until garlic is lightly browned.
Stir frequently.
Add liquids and seasonings.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add clams last 5 minutes.
Serve over linguine.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Brown meat.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except flour and milk.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine flour with 1 cup of the milk.
Stir into soup mixture.
Boil a minute or so.
Add remaining milk and heat, stirring frequently.
Do not boil after adding milk.

title: heavenly broiled fish
directions: Place fillets in a single layer on a well-greased baking platter. Brush fish fillets with juice. Combine remaining ingredients. Broil fillets about 4-inches from heat source for 4 to 6 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Remove from heat and spread with cheese mixture.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains approximately 327 calories per servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake by directions in 13 x 9-inch pan.
When cake is done, poke holes in top.
Pour milk and cream of coconut on top of cake.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put Cool Whip and fresh coconut on top.

title: tootie fruity pops
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Fill each cup with about 1/4 cup of yogurt mixture.
Place cups in freezer until partially frozen, about 45 minutes.
Insert sticks. Freeze until firm, about 1 hour.
To serve remove from cups. Makes 10 Tootie Fruity Pops.

title: almond-coconut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine 1 cup flour and 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar; add butter.
Cut in until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake until crust is lightly brown, about 15 minutes.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water.
Meanwhile, cook onion in 3 tablespoons butter until soft.
Stir in soup, salt, pepper, cheese and carrots.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Toss bread stuffing, mixed with 1/2 cup melted butter and spoon over carrots. Bake in moderate oven (350°) until thoroughly heated, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Add cream to desired consistency.

title: manicotti
directions: Combine sauce, onion, and spices together and cook.
Cook pepperoni in skillet and drain.
Add to sauce.
Simmer for one hour.
Cook noodles in boiling water for 12 minutes, drain.
Mix cheeses and add egg.
Stuff noodles with cheese mixture.
Put a little sauce in bottom of 9x13-inch casserole dish or baking pan. Place stuffed noodles in pan and pour remaining sauce over top. Sprinkle top with additional Mozzarella cheese if desired.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: eddie murn's crab cakes
directions: Pick crabmeat, removing all shell fragments.
Gently mix with cracker crumbs.
Add egg, then the mayonnaise, mustard, Old Bay and other seasonings.
Combine all these ingredients, taking special care not to disturb the crabmeat.
Let mixture sit in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
Deep fry or broil in oven. Perfect with cole slaw.
Form into round cake balls.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and brown sugar.
In one bowl, beat eggs and add milk.
In another bowl, combine cornmeal and flour.
Dip tomatoes in egg mixture and then coat with cornmeal/flour mixture.
Heat oil in skillet and brown tomatoes on both sides.
Make sure the oil is hot enough before you begin frying.

title: moist 'n crispy chicken
directions: Put cereal, paprika, salt and pepper in a large plastic bag and shake to blend well. Brush chicken on both sides with mayonnaise and put 1 piece of chicken at a time in bag; shake to coat well.
Place on rack in broiler pan and bake at 425° for 10 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy and good frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, powdered sugar and milk in small bowl. Beat slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of mixer.
Mix well about one minute.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread on cake at once.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave rice krispie treats
directions: Spray large microwave bowl with Pam.
Place marshmallows in bowl.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Coat a wooden spoon with Pam. Stir cereal into marshmallows.
Spray hands with Pam and press into square or rectangular pan.
Makes 16 servings.

title: school made cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and raisins.
Mix butter, egg and milk.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in the warm water.
Add the milk mixture to the flour mixture.
Then roll into oblong shape and brush with some melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll jelly roll fashion and slice.
Let rise until soft (about 1 1/2 hours) to touch and bake in 400° oven until brown. Glaze with confectioners sugar, milk and butter mixture.
Roll real thin.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
When cool, add 1 teaspoon of salt, marshmallows and nuts.
Drop on foil or place in loaf pan and cut in squares.

title: hamburger pinwheels
directions: Cook onion and ground beef in fat until brown; season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire.

title: glenda's mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together.
Drain fat off. Grease 8 x 6-inch pan or larger.
Line with tortillas.
Don't let any stay above mixture you pour in.
Pour meat mixture over tortillas.
Mix together Ranch Style beans, chicken soup and enchilada sauce.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over bean mixture.
Add another layer of tortillas.
Pour tomatoes and pepper over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: upside-down fruit cake
directions: Cream together oil and honey.
Blend in milk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder until blended.

title: green chile pie
directions: Fry pork sausage and drain.
Slice green chilies.
Line an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with cooked pork sausage.
Cover with sliced Mozzarella cheese and sliced green chilies.
Top with whipped up eggs.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place olive oil in pot.
Add garlic.
When garlic is golden, add parsley.
Add chicken and brown on all sides over moderate flame.
When chicken is well-browned, add wine, pepper and salt. Cook until wine is almost evaporated.
Add water and simmer about 45 minutes until chicken is done.

title: hot italian bread
directions: Cut bread lengthwise.
Spread evenly with butter or margarine. Gently shake and spread liquid Italian dressing over butter and bake in 350° oven 10 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: cheesy fries
directions: Scrub
potatoes, leaving skin on.
Cut each potato into 8 wedges.
Melt
butter
in
large pie plate. Dip wedges into melted butter
and arrange in a donut pattern. Combine cheese and spices.
Sprinkle
evenly
over
potatoes.	Bake
at 375° until potatoes are just tender.

title: reduced fat key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place graham cracker crust on baking sheet.
Set aside.
Whisk together condensed milk, egg substitute and lime juice.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake until center looks set but still slightly quavery, like gelatin, about 15 minutes. Cool completely on wire rack.
Transfer to refrigerator and chill completely, about 1 to 2 hours.
Spread whipped topping over cooled pie.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: In skillet, saute until golden brown Ramen noodles (use 1 or 2 flavor packages to taste), butter, almonds and sesame seed.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Mix ingredients together.
Cover and let dough raise, punch down; let dough raise again, punch down.
Roll dough out and add a mixture of brown sugar, granulated sugar, melted butter and cinnamon.
Put rolls in greased pan and let raise until double.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Drop cabbage into boiling water and cook 5 minutes.
Drain, put half of the cabbage in a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with half of salt, sugar and pepper.
Add flour, cheese and half of margarine.
Top with remaining cabbage.
Sprinkle on the bread crumbs
mixed with 1 1/2 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: jackie's creme brulee
directions: In double boiler, heat 3 cups heavy cream with the vanilla bean.
In a bowl beat sugar with egg yolks until light and creamy. Remove vanilla bean and stir warm cream into the egg yolks carefully and slowly.
Return mixture to double boiler.
Stir constantly until the custard coats the spoon.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a medium bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk, water, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake 30 to 45 additional minutes, or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool at room temperature.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt; mix well until sugar is all melted.
Sift flour and cream of tartar together; add to mixture, then beat well.
Add soda, dissolved in warm water.
Spread into greased and floured jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn onto towel; spread jelly of choice and roll up quickly.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan by spraying with no-stick spray.
Empty Bix-Mix into large bowl.
Stir in water and beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack before slicing.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers with fine blade.
Mix sugar and vinegar and bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add pectin.
Add food coloring. Serve with roast pork or lamb or use as a spread for crackers by mixing with cream cheese.

title: beer batter potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes; rub with oil and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Crumble next 6 ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in beer.
Set aside.
Cut potatoes into wedges.
Dip in batter and deep fry (375° oil) until brown.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine peanut butter and butter and stir over medium-low heat until melted.
Remove from heat, stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour and baking powder; stir into mixture.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.
Makes 24 bars.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Spray
large
oblong
casserole
dish
with Pam.
Layer bottom of dish with dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with bacon
and place
on
top
of dried beef.
Mix sour cream and cream
of mushroom soup together.
Spread this mixture evenly over
wrapped chicken.
Bake
at 200° for about 4 hours.
The chicken will have a pinkish color when done, but does not need further cooking, as it will be well-cooked.

title: simple pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix both flours together with fork to blend.
Add flour, alternately with milk.
Add the vanilla or 2 teaspoons vanilla and 1 teaspoon lemon.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°, then 10 minutes at 400° to brown.

title: five hundred degree roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Season meat with meat tenderizer and put garlic puree on top; sprinkle with pepper.
Place meat on a rack in a roasting pan.
Bake at 500° for 5 minutes per pound.
Turn oven off, leave meat in oven 2 hours.
Meat will be perfectly pink in center and delicious.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake until well done, 60 to 65 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain oranges.
Do not drain pineapple.
Stir oranges, pineapple, pecans and 1/2 tub
of Cool Whip thoroughly.
Stir Jell-O and boiling water until Jell-O dissolves.
Pour Jell-O into fruit and Cool Whip mixture.
Stir until smooth (no Cool Whip lumps).
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate.
Top with remaining Cool Whip when Jell-O has set.

title: crunchy ham sandwich
directions: Spread 2 slices of bread with mustard.
Add ham, cheese and tomato slices.
Cover with other spreaded slice of bread.
Mix together egg, milk and salt.
Dip sandwich in egg, milk and salt mixture, then coat with crushed corn/potato chips.
Cook sandwich on both sides in a hot, oiled skillet until golden brown.
Makes 2 sandwiches.
You will fine this makes a crunchy sandwich on the outside and a meal inside.

title: zucchini pizzas
directions: Over medium heat, melt the margarine in a large skillet.
Beat the egg and water together.
Slice the zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip each slice into the egg-water mixture, then cover the entire piece with flour.
Fry each slice until golden brown. Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Place a tablespoon of sauce or ketchup on each slice and sprinkle with the grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: diet formula(dr. dole's)
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator.
Drink 5 to 6 equal feedings during the day.
Contains 900 calories, 24 grams protein, 25 grams fat, 31 grams carbohydrate.

title: old fashion tea cakes(roll and cut cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large mixing bowl combine all the ingredients and beat until well mixed.
This will be a sticky thick mixture.
Dough will roll easier if divided into 2 or 3 portions.
Place each portion on well floured surface, sprinkle a little flour on top of dough and roll out to a thickness of about 1/4 inch.
Cut with 3 inch cutter, space cookies about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 7-10 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Yield:
36 large cookies.

title: asparagus with sunshine sauce
directions: If using fresh asparagus, cook lower stalk pieces, uncovered, in 1-inch boiling salted water, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add tips; cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes longer.
Drain.

title: layered green salad
directions: Cook bacon and crumble in bits.
Place 3 cups lettuce on bottom of a covered bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Layer in order peas, bacon, onion, crumbled eggs and Swiss cheese.
Add last 3 cups lettuce on top.
Spread 1 cup mayonnaise on top of lettuce to seal edges.
Cover tightly and chill for 24 hours.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with paprika and toss.

title: fast and fishy
directions: Press water from tuna.
Flake into small pieces in bowl. Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package.
Saute onion in oil until light brown.
Add tuna and chicken, simmer, covered, for 3 minutes.
Add macaroni and cheese.
Stir, heat and serve. Serves 4.

title: greg's pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and pudding mix together.
Stir in oil and ginger ale.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan or two 8-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream the eggs, 1 cup sugar and oil.
Add 1 cup flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sour cream.
Mix into creamed mixture. Dough will be heavy.
Stir in rest of flour.
Spoon dough in a well-greased tube pan.
Spread to just cover bottom.
In a separate bowl, combine the last 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Alternate dough and sugar-cinnamon mixture, ending with cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Lower to 300° the last 15 minutes.

title: moist pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and water in butter for 20 minutes, covered.
Stir occasionally.
Beat 4 eggs.
Add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Add raisins and nuts.
Place in a buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: spaghetti with broccoli and garlic sauce
directions: Blend oil, garlic, basil and cheese in blender.
Pour over hot macaroni.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cut crab delights in half or shred.
Combine crab, celery, mayonnaise and onions.
Serve on a sandwich or on lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: pink grapefruit gelatin
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium nonaluminum saucepan; stir well.
Sprinkle gelatin over mixture and let stand 1 minute. Stir well.
Place over medium heat; cook until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly.
tags: freshly squeezed pink grapefruit juice with pulp

title: depression plant
directions: Pour all ingredients over coal in order given.
Watch it grow. Red stuff can be food coloring or merthiolate.

title: apricot filled cookies
directions: Beat sugar, butter and salt on medium speed until fluffy.
Add yolks, cream and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes.
Gradually add flour, stirring with wooden spoon until smooth.
Form into ball; divide into 2 parts and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: boston creme candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts; boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, to soft-ball stage.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Add nuts.
Beat until starting to thicken.
Pour into buttered dish.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: caramels
directions: Measure sugar, corn syrup, cream and butter into large, heavy saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally.
When mixture begins to "caramelize," reduce heat and cook to firm ball stage (244°).
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into one corner of buttered 8-inch square pan.
Allow mixture to level of its own accord.
Let stand until cool.
Turn out onto board.
Mark off into squares.
Cut with buttered sharp knife.
Wrap individually. Yields 1 1/4 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook together in a skillet the onion, celery and mushrooms, then add cream of mushroom soup.
Set aside.
Put in layers:
layer of onion mixture, layer of rice, layer of broccoli and cauliflower, then cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: julie's potatoes
directions: Fry potatoes in
butter
until	crisp.	Pour
water and chicken bouillon over fried
potatoes
in pan and simmer until they heat through.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions and peppers.
Saute 2 minutes.
Set aside and remove from skillet.
Saute beef sprinkled with garlic powder.
Stir until brown.
Add tomatoes and broth or bouillon cubes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Blend together cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Stir into meat and cook until thickened.
Add onions and peppers and heat.

title: microwave chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Microwave bark until hot.
Dip pretzel in hot mixture; place on wax paper to cool.

title: butterfinger torte
directions: Lay 4 slices of cake side by side in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix chopped nuts and candy bars together and set aside.

title: sandies
directions: Cream 1 cup of butter or margarine and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar; add vanilla and water.
Add sifted enriched flour; mix well and add pecans.
Form into small rolls 1 1/2 inches long.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven (300°) for 20 minutes or until delicately browned.
While hot, roll
in confectioners sugar. Makes 3 dozen.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fix in layers as listed in dish and top with grated cheese. Cover dish with foil and cook 1 hour 20 minutes at 375°.

title: creole roast
directions: Mix together allspice, onion and lemon juice.
Rub mixture on roast, then pat with flour.
Brown on all sides.
Add chopped tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken kiev
directions: You will need round toothpicks.

title: jean's chapel windows
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips together.
Add eggs. Then add nuts, sifted powdered sugar and marshmallows.
Divide in half. Put
each
half
on waxed paper while still warm and roll into log.
Chill until firm and then slice.
Refrigerate.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel, slice and de-seed oranges; cut away all white membranes. Mix sliced oranges with sliced bananas and coconut. Chill mixture for several hours. Whip the cream; stir into fruit mixture before serving.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown meat with large onion; drain.
If desired, add liquid hot pepper to taste.
Spread beans in shallow, 10 x 15-inch pan. Top evenly with meat.
Sprinkle chilies over meat.
Cover evenly with shredded cheese.
Drizzle taco sauce over cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix half of the sugar with eggs and other half with melted butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put pie crust in the oven for a few minutes before pouring in filling.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes.
Makes 1 large pie.

title: snickers cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg. Add all other ingredients (except candy bars) and mix well.
Cut candy bars into tiny pieces.
Fold into cookie dough.
Chill dough. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: annie's own french dressing
directions: Mix all together until creamy.
A blender works well.

title: crunchy beef bake casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Combine all ingredients except onions.
Pour half the mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Add 1/2 can onions.
Pour remaining mixture over onions.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: egg-tuna bites
directions: Peel eggs; slice lengthwise and discard yolks.
Mix tuna until finely flaked; add parsley, lemon zest, mayo and pepper.
Mix well. Fill each egg half with 2 teaspoons tuna mix.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: italian tortilla stacks
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce mix, salt, tomatoes, sauce, water and chiles.
Blend well, simmer slowly 10 minutes.

title: speedy quiche
directions: In a large frypan, fry onion in butter; add ham, mushrooms and beaten eggs.
Scramble until soft set.
Then pour in cheese sauce; put in sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 10 minute bars
directions: Melt butter or margarine and mix into brown sugar and oatmeal. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Spread over top and refrigerate.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil for one minute.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and mix.
Press into a large greased cake pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread over the bars and chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together well and roll out thin.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese by creaming well.
Add chopped beef; mix well.
Add onions and salt.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Can be rolled in chopped nuts, if desired.
Serve with assorted snack crackers.
Recipe is doubled.

title: braised turkey breast with apple
directions: Cut turkey into 2-inch pieces.
Heat butter, oil and garlic in heavy skillet.
Brown turkey pieces, a few at a time, over medium to high heat.
Remove browned pieces to heavy pot with tight fitting lid.
When all pieces are browned, add brandy, if used, to skillet to deglaze.
Add wine or broth, stirring up all brownings. Pour over meat in pot.
Add parsley and thyme; cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into cubes.
Mix all ingredients and coat potatoes.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in baking dish and add coated potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove foil and turn potatoes.
Bake another 1/2 hour.
You can add more butter when you turn potatoes if they appear dry.

title: chocolate sheet cake and frosting
directions: Mix flour and sugar in large bowl.
Bring to boil:
oleo, Crisco oil, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour and sugar in bowl while hot and stir in eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, soda and buttermilk.
Mix and pour into pan, greased and floured (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: southwestern cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, or until delicately browned.

title: turnip greens with sliced turnips
directions: Wash greens good and
slice up or quarter turnips.
Put into boiling
water
with ham hock for flavor.
Bring to boil, cut heat to simmer and cook slowly until tender.
Add salt to taste and about
3 pods of hot pepper.
Serve with corn bread and I like to add pepper sauce.

title: drunken dogs
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together in order given.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Let cool and spread a small jar of marshmallow cream on top of cake.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain maraschino cherries well and lay on paper towel.	Mix sugar, condensed milk, butter and vanilla.	Knead thoroughly until like soft dough.
Roll fondant around the cherries until a ball (dust palm of hand with powdered sugar).
Lightly freeze balls as they dip better into the chocolate bark.
Melt chocolate bark in microwave and dip cherries.
Lay on buttered plate to cool.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in rolled oats, nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: great chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving size pieces.
Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in a bowl.
Dip each piece of chicken in sauce and place in crockpot.
Pour remaining sauce over top. Cook on low for 6 - 8 hours or on high for 3 - 4 hours.

title: lord charlies corn chowder
directions: Brown bacon, onion and celery.
Add chicken stock, salt, white pepper, thyme, potatoes and corn.
Simmer 1 hour.
In separate pan, melt butter, flour and half and half.
Whip smooth and add to soup.
Cook 10 minutes to blend.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons Parmesan, oregano, garlic and pepper; roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange in 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake 20 minutes more.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Shake vigorously before serving.
Makes about 1 cup dressing.

title: pineapple-pepper cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into ball.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to enhance flavor.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Using electric mixer, cream softened butter and sugar.
Add chocolate slowly.
Then add eggs, one at a time, beating five minutes on high between each egg.
Stir in vanilla and pour into a prebaked and cooled pie crust.
After an hour, top with Cool Whip or real whipped cream.
Chocolate curls or shredded chocolate may be added.
Refrigerate overnight to set.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Orange Cocoa: Empty cocoa mix into a large mixing bowl. Blend very well with a whisk. Place mix back into jar. Place 1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons mix into a cup. Add 1 cup boiling water. Stir until mixture is completely dissolved. Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: mom's barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan, just to melt butter.
Pour over already browned meatballs.
Place dish in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Leftover sauce may be frozen and used again.
Great with mashed potatoes!

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add flour and red pepper.
Mix well and add Rice Krispies.
Mix and shape into balls, then press down with a fork.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: foolproof flaky pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl and mix with fork.
Add shortening and mix with fork until mixture is crumbly.
In small bowl beat with fork the water and egg.
Combine the two mixtures until all are moistened.
Divide dough into 5 portions.
Wrap and chill for at least 1/2 hour.
Unused portions store well in freezer.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Combine sugar
and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients
and
stir
into egg mixture.
Stir in apples, nuts and
vanilla.
Pour
into
buttered spring-form tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Remove from pan. Top with brown sugar glaze.

title: oatmeal muffins(lo-fat, lo-sugar)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and melted oleo, just enough to combine.
Bake in greased pans at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pizza margherita
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Heap the flour in a mound on a board; make a well in the center and pour in the dissolved yeast.
Add enough extra water to mixture to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover with a towel and let rise in a large bowl until doubled in volume.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except crab meat.
Mix with electric mixer until blended.
Fold in crab.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes(low-fat)
directions: Sauce:
In saucepan, stir together milk, flour, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook; stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in onion.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook 1/2 bag of noodles according to directions.
Drain about 4 minutes.
Pour noodles into 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in a tablespoon chunk of butter while noodles are still hot, then stir in tuna, cream of chicken soup and milk. Mix well.
Crush about 20 to 30 crackers in a Baggie and pour over top of noodles.
Put in oven and bake uncovered, about 1/2 hour or until cracker topping is golden brown.
Makes about 4 medium servings.

title: broiled fish with butter
directions: Melt butter.
Add juice and salad mix.
Place fish on broiler pan.
Brush with seasoned butter mixture.
Broil 5 minutes.
Brush again.
Broil 5 more minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add chocolate chips, pecans, flour and vanilla.
Add margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Refrigerate to set.

title: shrimp stew
directions: Chop & saute pepper & onion in butter until tender in a dutch oven.
Add flour and cook until golden brown.
Add a quart of water bring to a boil.
Simmer for an hour until onions and bell peppers disappear.
Gravy will be very thin.
Add shrimp & cook slowly for about 15-20 minutes until shrimp is done.
Serve over rice.

title: pink christmas salad
directions: Place pineapple in large saucepan.
Add Jell-O; heat until Jell-O dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam spray.
Layer all ingredients, except chicken, in order given, ending with onion soup.
Top with chicken breasts.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
(I combine my soup and water before pouring over rice.
This is a good, low-fat low cholesterol meal when served with salad and garlic bread.)

title: fudge nut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Microwave or Melt chocolate and margarine on "high" for 2 min.
Stir until chocolate is completly melted.
Stir in sugar until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 8x8-inch baking pan.
Bake 35-38 min. or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: bean bake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix in four round thin layers or two layers.
Mix together 2 cups sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
Spread the remaining on top and between layers. Gently fold a large container of Cool Whip into the set aside cup of mixture.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle coconut on top and sides.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix in a large stock pot.
Add cukes and bring to a boil. Seal in hot jars.
(No need to process due to high vinegar content.)

title: bean soup
directions: Chop and saute onions and pepper in bacon grease and add to other ingredients.
Add 2 cans water.
Cook about 45 minutes.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Cut together flour, chopped nuts and margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: fresh cauliflower salad
directions: Be sure tomatoes are chilled before stirring into the salad.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and chill. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of pan.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream, cheese, onion and 1 stick of butter.
Heat and pour over potatoes.
Crumble cornflakes over this and drizzle other stick of butter over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: baked bunny bread
directions: Grease two cookie sheets.
On a lightly
floured bread board, cut dough into four equal sections.
Each section will make a bunny.
To make each bunny, divide one section in half.
Shape one half into a large oval for the bunny's body and place it on a cookie sheet.
Divide the other half in half again.
Form a round head with one piece and place it above the body on cookie sheet. Divide the other piece in half again.
Shape two ears from one half and make arms and legs from the other half.
Attach them to the bunny.
Place two bunnies on each cookie sheet, spacing them well apart, then brush the bunnies with the egg.
Loosely cover them with plastic wrap and let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in casserole dish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan with slices of bread, buttered side up.
Spread the browned sausage evenly over the bread.
Sprinkle the cheese over the sausage, then mix the remaining ingredients together and spread over the cheese. Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken enchiladas with green sauce
directions: Poach chicken in salted water until tender.
Tear meat into bite size pieces.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in 1/2 cup light cream and onions; add chicken and mix.
In blender combine chilies, pepper, tomatillos, garlic, cilantro and chicken stock; blend until smooth.
Add the remaining 1 cup cream, egg and salt to taste.
Blend.
Soften tortillas in hot oil.
Place 1/4 cup chicken mixture on each, roll and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil.
(They may be refrigerated or frozen at this point.)
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or longer if cold, covered.
Remove the foil and pour the sauce over enchiladas.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pecan christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix raisins, nuts and 1/4 cup flour.
Sift remaining dry ingredients.
Alternately fold in raisins, pecan mixture and dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Spoon into greased and paper lined pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 50 minutes in 10-inch tube pan.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: ground beef and vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil; simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: italian noodles
directions: Cut onion in small pieces and fry golden brown; remove and fry hamburg.
Combine all ingredients and place in a greased casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Grease 12-inch skillet lightly.
Add the chops and brown both sides over medium-high heat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add choice of liquid; reduce heat to low and simmer 45 minutes.
